title: pineapple coconut crescent desserts
directions: In small bowl, blend cream cheese and powdered sugar; stir in pineapple, nuts, orange peel and vanilla.
Separate dough into 8 pieces.
Place each piece in ungreased muffin cup; press dough to cover bottom and sides, forming 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon 1 teaspoon coconut into each cup.
Spoon 1 tablespoon pineapple mixture into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut; bake an additional 3 to 8 minutes until crust is brown.

title: "frozen fruit salad"
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon.
I put in cupcake liners.
Put on cookie sheet or, if you prefer, use 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
When frozen, put in Ziploc bag.
Take out as needed.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Lay a few strips of bacon on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of asparagus or zucchini soup
directions: Discard coarse ends from asparagus or trim and slice zucchini thickly.
In saucepan, bring the vegetable, onion, broth, salt, pepper and basil to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Empty all into blender; cover and blend on high speed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 55 minutes in 4 pie shells.

title: hot breakfast bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and unbeaten egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to first mixture.
Pour into greased oblong pan.
Mix currants, cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Break in pieces and serve warm with butter.

title: country captain
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper and brown well.
Remove from pan, but keep it hot.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour and blend well.
Add cocoa, vanilla and nuts and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes.
(Sift cocoa with flour.)

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Put into cookie press, using your favorite shape.
Squeeze on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes (until slightly brown). Let cool before removing.

title: beef a la deutsch
directions: Brown meat, add tomato sauce, etc. and cook 45 minutes. Combine cooked noodles and cubed cream cheese and stir to melt. Add sour cream and green onions.
Layer meat, noodles and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, salt, shortening and sugar until crumbly. Beat together with fork egg, cold water and vinegar.
Combine both mixtures.
Divide into 5 portions.
Shape into patties and wrap in wax paper and chill 1/2 hour before using.
Can be frozen for later.
Will keep for long time in freezer.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and let stand.
Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add all wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Use a square cake pan and alternate a layer of apple mixture, then a layer of batter mixture until each is used up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage - bean soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, saute onions, celery and potatoes in oil 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in cabbage and add chicken broth, garlic and seasonings.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in beans.
Cook 10 minutes longer for beans to heat through.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: durango hot dip
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Spread into 8-inch pie plate or casserole.
Bake about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with taco chips.

title: popsicles
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, jello and sugar.
Pour boiling water over; stir until dissolved.
Add the cold water.
Pour into Tupperware popsicle holders.
Makes approximately 18.

title: cornmeal-blueberry pancakes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, sugar and baking powder together.
In mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture and stir just until the flour is blended in; do not overmix.
Stir in blueberries.
Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Spoon about 1/3 cup batter into skillet and spread it to make a pancake 4-inches across.
Cook the pancake on the first side until bubbles begin to form and underside is well browned; turn pancake over and repeat.
Enjoy!

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs and milk together well.
Roll into balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. While meatballs are browning, mix the rest of ingredients together in a saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over the meatballs in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes at 350°.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion.
Pour off excess grease.
Add chili powder and salt.
Stir well.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Spoon into 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer beans, cheese and tortillas over meat.
Pour tomato liquid over cheeses. Chop tomatoes and chilies; spread over cheese.
Spoon soup evenly over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Following day, bake, uncovered, for one hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: monkey bread
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: cheryl's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients except margarine in a bowl.
Melt margarine in 8 or 9-inch pan and pour into bowl. Mix by hand.
Pour mixture into the square pan and bake 25 minutes.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Arrange chicken in a casserole. Salt and pepper.
Heat soup and water in pan until well mixed.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in microwave for 30 minutes or in oven until chicken is done (350° for 30 to 40 minutes).

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature; whip 3 minutes.
Add garlic, Italian seasoning and bacon bits.
Mix well.
Carefully add celery, olives and Longhorn.
Chill and form into one or two balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chinese chicken wings and drumettes
directions: Marinate the wings and drumettes overnight.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, nutmeg and walnuts, then add mayonnaise to taste.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Cut artichokes into small pieces.
Combine with other ingredients and spread into a small porcelain baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread on crackers.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix together all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers, slivered almonds and 1 stick melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange candied pecans
directions: Mix sugar with orange juice and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat to hard ball stage.
Stir in pecans and orange rind to coat.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut the potatoes in half or quarters. Put into a bowl with the olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic. Toss until potatoes are well covered. Dump potatoes on a baking sheet; spread out to make one layer. Roast in the oven for 1 hour or until brown and crisp. Flip potatoes within the hour to ensure browning. When done, toss parsley over potatoes, then serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Pour/mix Eagle Brand milk, limeade and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Add food coloring, if desired, and lime juice (if you like it tangy!).
Pour into crusts.
Pies should be frozen for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: butterflied leg of lamb (grilled)
directions: Combine wine, soy sauce, garlic, mint, rosemary and pepper and pour over the lamb in a shallow glass baking pan.
Refrigerate, covered, for 6 hours, turning frequently.
Preheat the grill. Drain the meat but reserve the marinade.
Grill the lamb 4 inches above the coals about 20 minutes on each side, basting frequently with the marinade.
After 30 to 40 minutes, check for doneness. When done, cut into thin slices and serve.

title: swedish christmas ham
directions: Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold in mustard and chives.
Makes 1 cup.

title: peanut butter patties
directions: Melt chips and paraffin in deep narrow bowl.
Spread each vanilla wafer generously with peanut butter.
Using tongs, dip each wafer into melted chocolate.
Handle with care and place each patty on a buttered sheet of foil or wax paper.
Cool.
They are ready to eat as soon as the chocolate is set.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Mix together.
Add 1 can desired fruit.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: taco bell nachos
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place tortilla chips on a cookie sheet. Spread beans on each chip.
Top with cheese, olive and onion. Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve with bowl of salsa.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: betty's cheesy beef casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions and set aside to drain.
Cook macaroni and set aside also.

title: christmas pudding 2
directions: Mix together and cook for 4 to 5 hours.
Makes 3 puddings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Stir carefully, just enough to dampen the dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (large). Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 18.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
While cooking, add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender, then drain off water.
Combine soup, water and sour cream; mix well. Combine meat, noodles and soup mixture in large pan.
Let simmer for 5 to 8 minutes over heat.
Serve.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well and add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla. Mix well and spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of hot cake and let stand for 15 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Put large and small mixer bowls and beaters in refrigerator until very cold, overnight is good.

title: french green string bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans into a casserole dish and evenly spread. Thoroughly mix 2 cans of golden mushroom soup through the beans until evenly mixed through.
Place the onion rings all over the top of the casserole.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, butter, brown
sugar
and
beaten
egg yolks; gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thick and smooth. Add vanilla; pour into baked
pie shell.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar,
spread
over
pie.
Place
in oven at 300° for 15 minutes until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use double boiler to melt candy.
Be sure water in boiler is not boiling, as candy will stick to boiler.
When melted, fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: new potatoes in cream
directions: Scrub the potatoes and scallions.
Cut the potatoes in quarters and the scallions in 1/2-inch pieces.
Put them in a saucepan and dust with flour.
Add the milk, cream, butter, salt and white pepper.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 20 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally until done.
Sprinkle generously with dill or parsley.
Serves 6.

title: russian potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Fry in 1/16-inch oil until golden brown and crisp, 3 to 4 minutes each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream, applesauce and/or grape jelly.

title: southwest corn muffins or bread
directions: Corn muffin mix is the base of a colorful cornbread, textured and flavored with the additions of corn, smoked cheese, chili peppers and ripe olives.
In the Toledo Blade test, this recipe was baked in a loaf pan to yield attractive slices.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and put in a large bowl. Add milk and half of the melted butter, fold in egg, cottage cheese, cream cheese, and onions.
Place in a greased baking dish. Combine crackers and remaining butter and sprinkle over the potato mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 350 degree oven for 20-30 minutes, or until crackers are lightly browned.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oats and oleo.
Put together in order written.
Sprinkle last mixture on top.
Bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°) for about 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and almond extract. Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top of batter.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, mixing well.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Stir dry ingredients and nuts into sugar mixture until well combined.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 24 squares.

title: butter pecan fruit whip
directions: Sprinkle pudding over Cool Whip; stir well.
Let set for a few minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
If thick after sitting, add a little more fruit cocktail juice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, dry and cut green tomatoes in thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Sprinkle with freshly ground black pepper.
Dredge in corn meal and fry in hot fat until lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy company cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, prepare and bake cake mix using package directions.
Pierce warm cake with a fork.
Spread sweetened milk then caramel topping over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with crushed candy.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cool shrimp and chop in small pieces.
In bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add other ingredients and stir good.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Put in pretty cut glass bowl on crystal tray and place crackers on tray.

title: strawnana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, strawberries, bananas, orange rind and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add mixture of flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Stir just until moistened.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Yield:
2 loaves.

title: miracle pie
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch deep dish glass pie plate.
Pour all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased cake pan and bake for about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Place cooked spaghetti noodles in a deep dish baking pan (packed).
Place pizza sauce on spaghetti, then cheese and toppings of your choice.
Place in oven and bake at 400° until cheese melts and toppings are hot.
Serve pizza lukewarm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 1-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together to form batter.
Pour into melted margarine.
Pour peaches on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Wash and chop vegetables; toss in large salad bowl.
Add cheese and Thousand Island dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Drain the browned ground beef and add it to the salad.
Crush Doritos and add to the salad.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl put 1/2 torn greens.
Make sure they are clean and dry.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer sliced boiled eggs and a little salt on that layer.
Next layer, in order, thawed peas, remaining greens or different kind, bacon and cheese. Spread mayonnaise over top, clear to the edge of the bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add 2 bunches of diced green onions and a little paprika, then toss and serve.
Serves 12 to 15.
This is very good and keeps for parties.

title: refrigerator pickles(bread and butter type)
directions: Toss cucumbers and onions together and place in a gallon container with tight-fitting lid.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with onion, celery and carrot until tender. Reserve vegetables. Chop chicken (you should have 4 cups).
Saute pepper in butter in a large skillet.
Mix in flour until smooth. Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese until melted. Cut off heat. Add pimento, soup, mushrooms, chicken and reserved vegetables. Add soy sauce and seasonings, then spaghetti.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken stuffed crescents
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients. Join and roll out 2 triangles of crescent rolls to form a square (total of 4 squares). Spoon equal amounts of mixture onto each square. Bring corners of squares to center and twist. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with 1 tablespoon of butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Mix salad dressing, sour cream, raisins, vinegar, onion, sugar and cheese.

title: parkway salad dressing
directions: Combine and blend 15 minutes.

title: frosting for german chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and chopped pecans/walnuts.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the chips with the milk.
Heat over medium-low heat, stirring until chips are melted.
(Be careful not to burn or scorch.)
Remove from heat.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Spread in a well-buttered 9-inch square pan. Refrigerate about 2 hours, or until firm.
Cut into small squares. Yield: 2 pounds.

title: imp of satan
directions: Blend margarine, cheese, pepper and Tabasco.
Add flour and cereal.
Chill; form into small balls.
Place on baking sheet and flatten with fingers.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 95 small imps.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Makes 1 quart dry mixture.
To make 1 cup tea, mix 2 spoons of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients together including juice from clams in mixer and beat until smooth.
Refrigerate and serve cold with chips, pretzels, etc.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Beat eggs; add to macaroni.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add powdered sugar.
Then slowly add in Cool Whip.
Will be thick.
Place in pie crust, then top with pie filling.
Sprinkle top with extra graham cracker crumbs or chopped nuts.

title: skewered sausages
directions: Cook over grill, brushing often with sweet and sour sauces.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and cook on 350° until golden brown.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water overnight. Drain.
Put peas and ham bone in water.
Add onions and celery.
Bring to boil and simmer slowly, stirring occasionally until peas disintegrated and turned to mush. Add seasonings.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: english toffee
directions: Use candy thermometer.
Cook in heavy iron frying pan.
Cook sugar and butter to soft crack on thermometer.
Put in nuts and vanilla.
Stir mixture well.
Pour out on large pizza pan.
Cool and break into small pieces.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into patties.
Layer patties in wax paper before freezing.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Blend powdered sugar and margarine together.
Combine peanut butter and graham crackers with this mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on the peanut butter mixture in the pan.
Cool in refrigerator and cut in bars.

title: company potatoes
directions: Put thawed potatoes in an 11 x 17-inch pan with seasoning. Heat soup and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Put cheese and onion on top.
Top with bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.
Bake after removing from freezer, not before freezing.

title: creme brule
directions: Beat egg yolks with an electric mixer on high for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in white sugar.
Warm whipping cream in a saucepan on low heat until very warm.
Gradually add in beaten egg mixture, stirring constantly, and cook for about 5 minutes until thick.
DO NOT BOIL!
Pour into an ungreased pie plate; cover and chill for 2 hours.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and broil for 5 minutes.
Serve over fresh fruit slices and angel food cake or pound cake.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Note: You may use rib-eye steak or beef tenderloin.

title: roast leg of lamb a la russe(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Have butcher bone the lamb or do it yourself.
Peel fell from lamb and trim off any fat.
Sprinkle lamb out flat on waxed paper on kitchen counter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon rind. Sprinkle with the lemon juice and, with your hands, massage juice into meat.
Roll them up jelly-roll style and tie at 2-inch intervals.
Combine onion, carrots and celery and spread over the bottom of a large, shallow roasting pan.
Place rolled lamb on vegetables.
Pour bouillon over meat and vegetables.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 or 2 3/4 hours, depending on degree of doneness desired.
Baste frequently with pan juices. Transfer lamb to a heated platter and keep warm in a low oven (150° to 175°).
Bring pan juices and vegetables to the boiling point and skim off all grease.
Puree in a blender or food processor or push through a sieve.
Return to pan and add 1/2 to 1 cup white wine depending on consistency of the gravy you prefer.
Bring quickly to the boiling point, stirring constantly and cook for 1 minute. Carve lamb and place on a heated deep platter.
Spoon a little of the gravy over the meat and pass the rest in a sauce-boat, or if there is little gravy, spoon it all over the meat.

title: mirliton casserole
directions: Peel and parboil mirlitons. Saute onion in oil.
Add the mirlitons and pepper and cook until most of the liquid has cooked down.
Saute the shrimp until pink in color.
Add them to the mirliton mixture and cook until thick and smooth. Season to taste. Pour into a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
(Same procedure can be used for eggplant and squash.)

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Beat sugar, oil and egg together.
Add the remaining ingredients, alternating with 1 cup of boiling water.
Last, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes very thin batter.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 18 cupcakes.
Ice as desired.

title: glorified macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basic potato salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix lightly. Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Cook hamburger with onions; drain. Put into crock pot with cheese and salsa. Simmer until all ingredients are well blended and the cheese is melted. Serve with Nachos or taco chips for a snack or party treat. Kids love this!

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to box directions but cut water by 3 tablespoons.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour half of batter into pan; sprinkle Vienna Revel over batter.
Spread remaining batter over Vienna Revel.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick test is done.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Add hamburger.
Stir in both cans of mushroom soup and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with chips or onions.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually add egg.
Add onion, crackers and seasonings.
Put cracker crumbs on top, also.
Bake in 350° oven in buttered baking dish about 1/2 hour.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in greased Bundt pan.

title: mardi gras party cake
directions: Melt butterscotch in water and cool.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs separately; add.
Blend in melted butterscotch; add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in 2 pans at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool, but don't allow to thicken.
When cool, add rest of ingredients and stir.
Put in mold or molds and refrigerate.

title: party mints
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
I usually separate dough of cream cheese into 3 large balls, then add flavoring and food coloring.
That way, I have an assortment of mints from 1 batch. You may need to add more powdered sugar after flavoring and food coloring so dough will not be sticky.
Shape into tiny balls. Roll in granulated sugar and press into molds.
Let dry thoroughly overnight.
Freezes well.
Makes approximately 60 mints.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine water, salt, shortening and sugar in bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast.
Add egg and half of flour.
Beat well.
Stir in more flour to handle easily.
Grease top of dough. Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will keep 3 days or immediately shape into rolls after mixing.
Cover with a towel and let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased pan.
Brush with butter after baking.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May take more or less flour, depending on consistency.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will make either 2 thin crusts or 1 thick crust.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Peel and halve the apples, removing the core.
Slice thinly, do not place in water to preserve the color.
Grease on ovenproof dish and line with a layer of bread crumbs.
Dot with lumps of butter, sprinkle with sugar to taste and cover with a thick layer of apples.
Repeat until all is used up, finishing with a layer of bread crumbs.
Press well together, dot with butter and bake at 330° for about 30 minutes until the apples are cooked through. Cool and turn out of the form, decorating with whipped cream when quite cold.
The apple cake may also be served lukewarm with whipped cream.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Spray baking pan with Pam.
Boil chicken and cut in pieces. Spread broccoli on bottom of pan. Spread chicken on broccoli.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in greased baking dish.
Blend the next 4 ingredients over low heat.
Pour the sauce over potato mixture and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bean and cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in a bowl. Transfer to a 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Blend in corn.
Spoon evenly over bean mixture to within 1-inch of edge.
Bake until topping is golden brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all beans; toss beans with celery, green pepper and onion in a large bowl.

title: mama's cherry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for both top and bottom crust.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Mix together evaporated milk, mustard and black pepper.
Pour over lettuce and onion.
Toss and chill. In skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown and cook bacon.
Cool and crumble. Add vinegar and sugar to skillet and bring almost to boil. Pour over lettuce.
Top with crumbled bacon and serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Put mayonnaise in bowl; add water and sifted dry ingredients alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Allow to cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Dust with sifted confectioners sugar or frost with orange glaze (confectioners sugar, orange juice and butter).

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, salt, black pepper and onion.
Add 1/2 the egg and flour.
Mix.
If too soft to handle, add more flour.
With hands, form balls.
Roll in beaten egg then cracker crumbs.
Add oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Heat and fry croquettes, turning 3 or 4 times to brown on all sides.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into small balls.
Then roll in powdered sugar.
Store in covered container overnight in refrigerator.
These freeze well.
Can be made ahead.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit into a bowl.
Add pudding mix and Tang. Mix together by hand.
(Sometimes if you let it set for awhile, the lumps dissolve.)
Add fruit and chill.
(Add bananas last to make sure they don't turn.)

title: baked duck with mushroom rice
directions: Pick and wash duck thoroughly.
Rub 1/2 dry soup mix inside duck.
Stuff onion inside duck.
Rub rest of soup mix on outside of duck.
Lay duck on heavy-duty tinfoil and cover.
Place in pan and bake slowly (approximately 300°) until duck is tender (2 to 3 hours).
Approximately 1 hour before duck is done, combine mushrooms, rice and soup in baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When duck is cool, remove meat from bone and add to rice mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Return to oven for approximately 15 minutes to combine flavors.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread into 13 x 9-inch dish. Bake for 30 minutes. Top with 5.6 ounces French fried onions. Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: herbed limas and peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: onion casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole, place alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese. Pour mushroom soup and milk over the top of the onion mixture and it will cook through.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients with 2 cups of the shredded cheese.
Pour into a large baking dish and sprinkle the other cup of cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and drain.
Mix together with half jar enchilada sauce.
Layer tortillas (3) in baking dish, meat mixture and pour jar of enchilada sauce over top of meat.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Add another layer of 3 tortillas and pour 1/2 jar enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle rest of grated cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes to 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients except mayonnaise on medium heat, stirring often until thick.
Cool completely.
Add mayonnaise. Pour dressing over cold cooked macaroni.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir first five ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: toffee malt cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add pudding mix and vanilla. Combine the flour, oats, baking soda and salt.; add to creamed mixture. Fold in the malted milk balls and the toffee bits (dough will be stiff). Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter and graham cracker crumbs with powdered sugar.
Mix well and put in bottom of cake pan.
Let set 10 minutes, then pour in sliced bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and trim mushroom stems.
Cut mushrooms in half or one quarter the larger ones.
Heat oil in a large skillet. Add all ingredients (except parsley for garnish).
Simmer the mixture for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let mushrooms cool in liquid.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons.
Remove seeds.
Mix sugar, 2 cups hot water and lemon juice until sugar dissolves.
Finish filling gallon container with cold water.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer raw rice, corn, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce and water, then add ground chuck (raw), tomato sauce, water and bacon. Bake, covered, 45 minutes to 1 hour, then uncovered 15 minutes more.
This is something like Spanish rice.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook onion and sausage balls in skillet until onion is tender and sausage is lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat. Add next 4 ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add peas and pimento, cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Taste for seasoning. Some salt and pepper may be needed, depending on seasonings in sausage.
Serves
6 to 8.

title: exotic celery
directions: Boil celery 8 minutes, drain and mix with soup, pimentos and chestnuts.
Pour in casserole.
Sprinkle with onions and cashews. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a heavy skillet, brown and crumble sausage. Remove meat and drain well. Line a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with crescent roll dough. Press edges together to seal. Sprinkle the sausage and grated cheese over the dough.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in 1/4 cup white sugar, salt, 2 tablespoons oleo, egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Work in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place into greased bowl.
Turn greased side up and cover tightly. Refrigerate 1 hour or up to 4 to 5 days.

title: cheese-n-carrot casserole
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook and drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions.
Saute.
Add flour, salt and mustard.
Stir well.
Add milk.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Layer carrots and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Mix well.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy veggies
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick butter.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour. Mix vegetables, cheese, sour cream and sauteed onion.

title: campfire beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, and sugar. Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped walnuts. Use grapes with toothpicks to dip.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix Rice Chex, coconut, pecans, sugar and margarine well.
Put 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Top with softened ice cream.
Put remaining topping on.
Freeze until firm.
Take out 5 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions on box.
Saute shrimp or chicken with butter, salt, pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Add cooked vermicelli.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Blend cheese and margarine.
Add flour, pepper and mustard. Mix by hand, kneading into firm ball.
Add pecans and cereal. Blend well.
Roll into small balls and flatten on a well-greased, floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until firm and lightly brown around edges.
Makes about 7 dozen.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: crispy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Cream until light.
Add salt, vanilla, soda and flour. Blend well.
Pinch off pieces of dough (about size of walnut). Press with fork or glass.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: To Cook By Microwave:
Heat oil in 12 x 8-inch dish at High 2 minutes.
Stir in beef, garlic and ginger.
Cook at High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes; stir twice.
Add broccoli.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at High 5 to 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp; stir once.
Blend cornstarch with broth, sherry and soy sauce until smooth.
Stir into beef mixture.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Stir once.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oreo freak-out
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan in thin layer.
Slice soft vanilla ice cream, then push into cookies. Pour hot fudge (whole jar) over ice cream, then layer walnuts, then layer Cool Whip on top.
Freeze it, then enjoy!
Best if made night before.

title: cucumber appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add dressing mix.
Blend. Add dill.
Spread on bread slices.
Score cucumber lengthwise with a fork, then slice thin. Place one slice of cucumber on each slice of mixture/bread. Sprinkle with dill weed and paprika for color.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Place cucumber in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; add vinegar and water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 30 minutes in refrigerator and drain well.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, dill, sugar and pepper.
Stir into cucumbers.
Serve immediately or it will hold well until served.
Serves 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peggy's potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes ahead of time; undercook, you do not want them as soft as you would for eating.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from one jar of artichokes into a frying pan. (Discard marinade from second jar.)
Chop artichokes in food processor and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in the frying pan until limp (about 5 minutes).

title: cheese grits souffl
directions: In a large pot, put grits in 3 cups boiling water. Cook over low heat until very thick. Remove from heat and add butter. Stir until melted. Add salt and pepper. Stir eggs into milk. Add to grits and mix well. Add grated cheese. Pour into a deep 3-quart greased casserole and bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: 6-week muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt and sugar, being sure that baking powder is well blended.
Stir in the Raisin Bran, then the shortening, eggs and buttermilk.
Store in a tight container in the refrigerator.
Bake in greased muffin pans as desired at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Brown chicken; place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a skillet (used to brown
the chicken), add the soup and one soup can of water; bring to a boil.
Slowly add wine while stirring.
Simmer.
Add other ingredients while stirring.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 30 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and cook for another 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Add to creamed mixture.
Using teaspoon, drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.
One cup chocolate chips may be added (optional).

title: cake mix brownies
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Whisk in cake mix; stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 15x10x1 pan.
Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes.

title: roast beef hero sandwich
directions: Heat bread according to package directions.
Slice horizontally in half.
Combine mayo, mustard, olives and onion. Spread on bread.
Layer the beef and cheese on bottom half of bread.
Cover with bread top.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen passion
directions: Pour condensed milk and beverages into ice cream freezer container.
Process according to manufacturer's directions. Makes 2 quarts.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks. Dissolve soda in milk; add alternately with flour which has been well sifted.
Fold in beaten egg whites and blackberry juice.
Bake in oven at 350°.
Bake in layers or tube pan.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: *May substitute 1/2 cup grated processed cheese with dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: party pate
directions: In a bowl, mix all together and mash.
Chill and serve with crackers or party size bread.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Allow oleo and cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Make strips with cookie press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add shallots. Saute for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables; keep warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add water slowly.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and strawberries.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: vegetable soup of trieste
directions: Soak the beans in cold water to cover for 12 hours.
Drain and place in a saucepan with bacon fat and bay leaves.
Add the water and simmer for 1 hour.

title: turkey in honey-mustard sauce
directions: Cut turkey into stir-frying sized strips.
In skillet over medium high heat in hot oil, cook turkey 10 minutes or until browned; remove.
Pour off fat.
In small skillet, combine soup, orange juice, honey, mustard and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return turkey to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: smores
directions: Put cereal into a large bowl. Butter a 9 x 13 dish or pan. Melt 5 cups marshmallows, corn syrup, margarine and chips in a 3-quart pan over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal. Mix quickly until cereal is completely coated with chocolate. Stir in the other cup of marshmallows. Press mixture evenly in buttered dish or pan with buttered back of spoon. Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: apple german chocolate cake
directions: Place pie filling in a blender; cover and process until the apples are in 1/4-inch chunks.
Pour into a mixing bowl; add dry cake mix and eggs.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and then cut.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake, coating all potatoes.
Empty bag into a shallow baking pan (spray pan).
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in airtight container.
Put amount of mix in a cup of hot water to taste.

title: cornmeal and blue cheese squares
directions: Heat olive oil in a large pot.
Add onion and garlic and saute on medium heat until onion begins to soften, about 2 minutes.
Add liquid and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to simmer and add parsley, salt and pepper.
Slowly, in a thin stream, add cornmeal (sifting is even better).
Stir constantly until thick.
As cornmeal begins to pull away from sides of pan, add Blue cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Continue stirring to mix in the cheese.
Total cooking should be about 20 minutes.
Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch pan and spread evenly.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Cut into squares, diamonds or cutter shapes, if desired.
Serve warm.
Can be made ahead and reheated quickly under the broiler.

title: egg salad delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika and lettuce.
Toss gently.
Cover.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce. Sprinkle paprika.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Salt and pepper meat to taste.
Place all ingredients in a soup pot or crock-pot.
Flavor to taste. Cook until all raw vegetables are tender.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown hamburger with garlic and bell pepper; drain off all fat.
Add cheese (reserve 1/2 cup), tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans, drained. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: In large bowl, mix together meat, crumbs, onion, eggs, parsley and salt. Shape into 1 inch balls. Heat oven to 350°. In large skillet, brown meatballs in margarine; drain. Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Stir together jelly and barbecue sauce; pour over meatballs. Bake 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes approximately 6 dozen. Recipe may be made ahead. Cover; seal and freeze.
When ready, place in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours. Uncover; bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: grilled vegetable platter
directions: Mix the last 6 ingredients together.
One and 1/4 hours before serving, cut onions, potatoes, carrots and eggplant in half and place in boiling water.
Let simmer for 15 minutes or until
all vegetables
are
tender.
Add
mushrooms,
yellow peppers
and asparagus
to
precooked
vegetables.
Pour wine mixture
over vegetables in bowl.
Prepare grill for barbecuing.
Place
half the vegetables on grill, occasionally adding wine
mixture until vegetables are browned and tender.
Repeat with
remaining vegetables.
Place on a large platter and pour remaining wine mixture over vegetables.
Makes 8 servings.

title: russian pirogi
directions: Saute onion, carrots and cabbage in hot butter.
Remove from skillet.
In same pan, brown meat and lower heat.
Drain meat. Stir in water, gravy mix, parsley, salt, savory and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add to vegetables.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Then add pecans.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: candied yams and apples
directions: Combine apples and yams; pour into a shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over entire casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste the yams and apples occasionally with the syrup in the casserole. Serves 6.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Place apples in large mixing bowl; add sugar and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat eggs lightly and add to sugar apple mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add to apples, alternating with oil. Grease and flour pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced sesame bars(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices; set aside.
Beat egg; gradually add sugar and mix well.
Stir in butter.
Add dry ingredients.

title: thyme-lime chicken
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, melt butter in olive oil and lime juice, thyme, lime peel, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place chicken on a greased broiler pan.
Brush with sauce.
Broil, basting frequently.
Have broiler pan 6 to 7 inches from the heat for 15 to 20 minutes on each side or until chicken juices seem clear.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red corncob jelly
directions: Collect corncobs.
Cover with water and boil slowly for 1/2 hour.
Remove corncobs and drain juice.
Add Sure-Jell to the juice and bring to a hard boil.
Add sugar slowly and bring to a hard rolling boil; boil for one full minute.
Pour into jelly jars and skim foam off the top.
Pour hot paraffin to cover and store.

title: fruit cobbler(peach, cherry or berry)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup (1/2 stick) of margarine in a 9 by 13-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, sugar, milk, salt, and baking powder to form a batter.
Pour the batter over the melted butter.
Stir to mix. Spoon the fruit onto the batter.
Bake 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken zucchini
directions: Brown chicken
in
peanut or vegetable oil.
Add sliced zucchini
and
sliced
mushrooms.
Sprinkle
with sesame seed. Add about 1/3
cup
of	soy sauce and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with rice and fruit salad.
Serves 4.

title: grilled chicken tacos
directions: Preheat grill to medium heat. In small dish, combine cumin, salt and red pepper. Wash hands. Rub spices and 1 tablespoon oil onto chicken. Wash hands.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift cocoa with 1/3 cup sugar.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Combine shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Add soda to flour and sift 3 times.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Spray medium-large pot with Pam.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add chicken pieces; cook, but do not brown.
Season with oregano and salt.
Add green chiles, beans and potatoes.
Bring to heavy simmer.
Add white pepper.
When potatoes are soft, mash to desired consistency.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and mix well. Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Stir in sifted soda, salt and flour.
Add oats. Form small balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake using directions for 13x9 cake pan. Pierce cake several times with handle of a wooden spoon. Mix caramel topping and condensed milk in a bowl. Pour over cake. Sprinkle with half the candy bar crumbs. Spread whipped topping over cake and sprinkle with remaining crumbs. I drizzle caramel and chocolate syrup over the top. Chill until serving time.

title: pickle wraps
directions: Dry ham on paper towel as well as the pickles.
Spread cream cheese on ham.
Roll pickle with ham.
Slice pickles up.

title: apple-nut coffee bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and soda; then set aside. In large bowl combine apple, sugar and coffee crystals.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring once.
Add egg and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in flour mixture just until combined.
Fold in nuts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir all together and refrigerate 2 hours before serving. Keeps good in refrigerator for a week, if lasts that long.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cook	the
spinach
following package directions.
Drain	well.
(Take
in hands and squeeze out excess water.) In
a large bowl, mix together the spinach, both cheeses and
egg.
Stuff
mixture into uncooked manicotti shells. Spread 1 cup spaghetti
sauce and the water in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish
or
larger
to hold all of the shells. Arrange the stuffed shells in the sauce-water, making 1 layer. Completely cover with	the remaining
sauce.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes until shells are done.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Beat in oil.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and blueberries.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until tests done.
Use 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch bread pan or 8-inch square pan.
Square pan will bake in 40 to 45 minutes.

title: linzer torte
directions: Mix flour and baking powder; cut in butter.
Add sugar, almonds, eggs and all other ingredients except apricot jelly. Knead to a smooth dough.
Take a spring-form and flatten 3/4 of dough into pan.
Spread jelly over dough.
Take rest of dough and use rolling pin to flatten dough.
Cut about 1/2 inch strips and lay crisscross over jelly.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain fat.
Add rice, soups and water.
Cook about 30 minutes on low heat.
Put in casserole dish and add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Cream sugar & eggs (one at a time).
Add seasonings to flour & mix with creamed sugar.
Add oil & mix very well.
Add nuts & fold in apples.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour in greased bundt pan.

title: strawberry buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in large saucepan.
Heat on stove until gelatin dissolves.
(Do not boil.)
Allow to cool.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix everything together except tortillas.
Spread small portion of ingredients onto the uncooked tortillas.
Don't spread to the end of the tortilla.
Roll up; slice 1 1/2-inch pieces and refrigerate overnight.
Pile high and watch them disappear.

title: pork creole
directions: Heat oil in heavy pot; slowly saute meat, bell pepper, onion and celery for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and blend in.
Add seasoning, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chicken broth.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: peppered steak
directions: Melt 1/4 pound oleo. Add steak which has been cut in strips. Add sliced onions, bell pepper and celery. Cook for a few minutes. Add soup and soy sauce. Add pimento and salt to taste.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add cornstarch if not thick enough.
Serve over potatoes or rice.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until firm. Shape into a ball. Can be rolled in additional pecans, if desired. Serve with graham crackers.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
To well beaten eggs, add sugar, vanilla wafer crumbs, coconut, nuts and margarine.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir oats, chocolate chips and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hot chicken salad(casserole)
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole and top with mixture of 1 cup Special K cereal and 1/4 cup slivered almonds, browned in butter. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake following box directions.
Poke holes in the finished cake.
Pour cream of coconut over the cake.
Layer the Cool Whip over the cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: chocolate satin frosting
directions: Blend sugar and hot water into chocolate.
With spoon, beat half of egg into chocolate mixture.
Beat in remaining 1/2 egg. Beat in butter, one tablespoon at a time.
Blend in vanilla or rum extract.
Frosting will be thin.
Place bowl in ice water and beat until spreading consistency.

title: cornbread or muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend with margarine.
Add milk and eggs; beat 1 minute.
Pour in 2 tablespoons oil in iron skillet. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until well done.

title: zupa grzybowa(mushroom soup)
directions: Wash mushrooms, slice and cover them with cold water for 2 hours.
Rinse bones and meat with cold water. Add the 1 1/2 quarts water to meat and vegetables.
Cook until both are tender. Strain meat and vegetables. Add stock to mushrooms. Simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with dumplings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into three pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust browns.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit well. Mix together with sour cream, marshmallows and coconut. Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: terrific meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.
Put in 7 x 10-inch pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: eggnog for a party
directions: Beat yolks until light in color.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add slowly the liquor chosen.
Beat constantly.
Let stand 1 hour. Beat 2 to 4 cups liquors and the whipping cream.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 hours.
Fold in egg whites.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in a baking dish. Combine ketchup and 1/2 the Coke.
Mix well. Spread over meat.
Pour rest of Coke around the meat (not on it). Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three-tiered omelet with wine sauce
directions: Beat yolks until light.
Add both salts, pepper, parsley, shallots and flour.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat egg whites together with wine until stiff but not dry.
Carefully fold whites into yolk mixture.
Grease three 8-inch pie plates.
Divide egg mixture between them.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until set.

title: herb pesto
directions: In food processor, chop nuts and garlic very fine. Add herbs, parsley and oil and process until just blended, about 30 seconds. This pesto can be added to marinades for grilled foods or used as a topper for hot pasta or boiled potatoes. Try it on grilled sandwiches in place of mayo.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then add flour, salt and milk.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar together with fork.
Mix egg, vinegar and water together and add to dry ingredients.
Mix to size of peas, roll into 2 balls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 30 minutes in freezer.
Lay out between 2 sheets of wax paper and roll out, or leave in freezer until needed.

title: grass river lodge meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well; place in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: apple cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, 1 cup sugar, vanilla, apple, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Shape into balls and roll in mixture of 4 tablespoons of sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Flatten with fork or bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter and brown onion and chicken.
After browning, add water to cover chicken 3/4 way.
Then simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine
sugar,
unbeaten egg whites, water and cream of tartar and salt in upper part of double boiler.

title: string beans in wine
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add string beans and mushrooms.
Chop garlic and onion.
Add white wine and cheese.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Simmer until string beans are tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt; sift into large bowl.
In small bowl, beat eggs with whisk (lightly); add buttermilk and mix well.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ones and stir together until smooth using a wooden spoon.
Do not overbeat.
Put a 9-inch ovenproof skillet over high heat for 1 minute until very hot.
Remove from heat and using brush, quickly coat bottom and sides of pan with melted butter.
Immediately pour in batter, smoothing top.
Bake in center of oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until it begins to pull from sides of pan and top is browned.
Cut into wedges and serve hot. Makes one 9-inch bread.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt.
Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir on low heat until thickened. Add vanilla.
Layer cookies and bananas with pudding mixture.

title: rob's special sunday pancakes
directions: With fork, crush banana in bowl.
Add egg substitute and oil. To pancake mix, add milk, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Stir with whisk; not too much.
Add banana mixture.
Whisk together, but not too much.
On a 375° griddle, add ladleful of mixture.
Makes a 6-inch pancake.
Garnish plate with sliced kiwi or peach slices. Best served with warm cane syrup.
Makes 6 or 7 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop cookies on greased cookie sheets.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lipton onion mushroom-vegeburger loaf
directions: In medium bowl, combine Lipton onion mushroom mix, water, Vegeburger, bread crumbs, egg, bell pepper, sage and basil. Place in loaf pan.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in banana.

title: crispy oven fried fish fingers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Oil 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, lemon peel, marjoram, paprika, thyme and garlic powder in shallow pan.
Combine lemon juice and wine in shallow pan.
Cut fish into desired size "fingers" or "sticks". Dip each finger into lemon mixture, then in crumb mixture, coating well.
Place fish fingers on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Drizzle with Crisco oil.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes on baking sheet.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 175 calories, fat 6 g (50 cal or 28% of total calories), sat fat 1 g (<5% of total calories), carb 7 g, protein 24 g, chol 60 mg and sodium 180 mg.

title: frozen cherry delight
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients (*add sugar if using raisins to make the bread or tea bread.
*Raisins are not added to soda bread when used as a main stay bread.)
Cut in shortening with pastry blend until the consistency of cornmeal.
(*Stir in raisins.)
Add buttermilk gradually until you have a dough not dry.
Knead dough for 1 minute or until smooth.
Shape into round loaf.
Brush with milk and cut a deep cross into loaf to prevent splitting.
Bake on greased sheet at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Shape into balls and brown. Serve with Kraft Barbecue sauce or make your own sweet & sour sauce by combining 1 cup mustard & 2 cups apple jelly. I prefer the apple jelly/ mustard sauce.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper, celery and onions.
Add 2 cups sugar and blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture immediately.
Allow to cool.
Store in refrigerator 24 hours before using.
Will last for awhile.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine corns, broccoli, onion and mustard.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no cook lasagna
directions: Brown beef and add spaghetti sauce; stir well.
(May add onions if you like.)
Crack eggs into a bowl and beat.
Add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup of shredded cheese.
Add oregano and mix well.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles in dish.
Put some meat mixture over noodles.
Add cheese mixture and then just layer.
Pour hot water into baking dish around edges.
Cover dish with foil.
Press foil to sides. Put dish in oven.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add rest of cheese on top before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch jelly roll pan with the graham cracker squares.
Mix margarine and brown sugar; spoon over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 350 degree oven for approximately 12 minutes.

title: midway caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and keep warm in large roasting pan in oven.
(I spray lightly with Pam.)
Combine remaining ingredients, except soda and nuts in 2-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Stir until brown sugar dissolves, then continue to boil to soft ball stage (234° to 235°).
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour hot syrup over popped corn and nuts, stirring to combine well.
Return to preheated 250° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir corn and repeat heating and stirring two more times.
Cool thoroughly on brown paper sack. Store in airtight containers in cool place.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix with hands.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounce package of chocolate chips and pour over top.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.
Keep cool.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Spicy: Substitute 1/8 to 1/4 teaspoon ground red pepper for black pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hard soap
directions: On the first day, combine grease, 20 gallons water and 4 cans lye.
Cook until grease is consumed.
On the second day, add 10 pints water and 2 cans lye to first days mixture.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's chocolate delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans. Press down into a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and top with 2nd layer.

title: squash dressing
directions: In mixing bowl, crumble cornbread mix with other ingredients. Pour in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together and mix together with flour, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts together.
Grease and flour large loaf pan (10 x 13-inch).
Put 1 layer batter, 1 layer cinnamon mixture, 1 layer batter and 1 layer cinnamon mixture. Bake 55 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies(fast and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and water together.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Top of cookie will look pale.
Cool 1 minute then remove to rack or plate.

title: esthers orange marmalade layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter two 9 inch round cake pans, line with parchment or wax paper, and butter and flour the paper, shaking out the excess.
In a bowl, sift the flour, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, beat the butter with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add the sugar, a little at a time, and beat the mixture until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, orange zest, and vanilla.
Beat in 1/3 of the dry ingredients alternately with 1/2 of the buttermilk until combined well.
Add half the remaining dry ingredients and the remaining buttermilk and beat until combined well.
Finally, beat in the remaining dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.

title: parmesan pepper sauce or dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Use as a salad dressing or dipping sauce for raw vegetables or pretzels.
Use warm as a dipping sauce for chicken fingers or wings.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water and cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled Jell-O to the cream cheese mixture. Fold in the Milnot.
Melt the Parkay and pour over 1/2 cup sugar and graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1/2 cup mixture.
Press firmly into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add the filling and sprinkle with reserved graham cracker crumb mixture. Refrigerate and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and chunk eggplant and cook in salted water until tender; drain. Cook bacon until crisp; crumble. Saut onions in some of the bacon drippings. Drain the tomatoes and add to the eggplant. Add grated cheese, beaten eggs, bacon and onion. Stir cornbread crumbs in last. Bake in greased baking dish at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: oven baked pancake
directions: Preheat oven very hot at 450°.
Beat eggs until foamy. Combine flour and baking powder, beginning and ending with flour and continuing to beat with mixer or food processor.
Swirl butter in 10-inch ovenproof skillet or shallow casserole, being certain to cover sides well.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fluffed or golden.
To remove, slide a spatula around the edge.
Slide onto warm plate.
Top with fruit preserves and sour cream.

title: bacon, lettuce & tomato soup
directions: Saute bacon
until
done.
Add	lettuce and saute until limp. Add flour
and
cook
about
1 minute.
Add water mixed with soup bases,
nutmeg and Tabasco sauce.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick,
about
10 to 15 minutes.
Add cream or milk and heat until warm.
Makes about 13 cups of soup.

title: apple tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 3 empty one pound coffee cans.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and raisins.
Core the apples and grate into flour mixture. In a saucepan melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir butter mixture into dry ingredients. Spoon batter into prepared cans.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until a cake tester or skewer comes out clean.
Cool in cans for 10 minutes. Remove from cans.
Cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: fish jello
directions: In
a
clear,
glass bowl, mix the green jello and sardines. In
same
manner
as
jello fruit salad, top with Cool Whip, mixed with sardine oil.
To carry out ocean motif, make Cool
Whip waves on jello and have fish sticking up like they are swimming. (No one will ever ask you to bring seafood to a covered
dish dinner
again,
even
if
you
are married to a shrimper.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix sugar and shortening in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in zucchini, water and eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaves before slicing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 300° and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion together. Add soup and water and stir.
Add rice and simmer 5 minutes.

title: peach almond pound cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Prepare the bottoms of 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in sour cream and peaches.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn out onto racks to finish cooling.

title: crackling bread
directions: Place
cracklings in heavy boiler and stir while cracklings heat.
Sprinkle
salt
on
them
and stir again.
Pour 2 cups boiling
water
over cracklings.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 3
to 5 minutes.
Gradually add finely ground cornmeal, while mixture
is
still
on stove.
Stir until a stiff batter is formed.
Drop from large spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake
in
a 450° oven until well browned (20 to 30 minutes).

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix well until blended.
Mash 3/4 cup strawberry slices.
Add to cream cheese mixture. Add confectioners sugar to cream. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture. Fold remaining strawberries into cream mixture and pour into crust. Chill overnight.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: Line miffin tins with foil or paper liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.

title: aunty rika's "applesauce spice cake"
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add applesauce and raisins.
Sift together next 5 ingredients; add to first mixture alternately with beaten egg.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
It's so good!!!!

title: sausage egg rolls
directions: Brown Sausage over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add 2 bags of cole slaw mix, ginger, garlic, pepper, salt; mix well.
Transfer to colander to drain.
Cool 15 minutes. Assemble egg roll wrapper as directed on package, using 1/3 cup sausage mixture for each roll.
Deep fry in 3 inches of cooking oil for 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: heath bar refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies with stick of melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: cauliflower delight
directions: Microwave cauliflower and water in a glass dish on High for 9 minutes.
(Drain water.)
Add all other ingredients in order and microwave on Roast (or Medium-high) for 2 minutes.

title: working woman's italian beef
directions: Pour ingredients in crock-pot over roast.
Add less than 1/4 cup of water to bottom.
Cook on low for 12 to 24 hours.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft and peaks form.
Add brown sugar in two additions, beating lightly after each.
Stir in nuts and drop 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for about 30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil, then waxed paper.
In small bowl, beat eggs for 5 minutes until thick; pour eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Gradually add sugar and mix at low speed.
Blend in water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour in pan, spread to corners.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn pan upside down on wax paper with confectioners sugar.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Crumble yeast.
Add warm water (1/2 cup), salt and sugar, then egg and shortening and 2 cups water.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Add flour to make stiff batter and beat 3 minutes.
Mix thoroughly. Place in greased bowl.
Cover with two layers of wax paper.
Place in coldest section of refrigerator.

title: trish's pork chops
directions: In electric skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat. Brown pork chops on both sides; season pork chops for personal taste.
Remove them from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Then brown flour in oil until light brown; mix Lipton onion soup mix with 2 cups water and pour in skillet.
Pat pork chops back in with the potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat setting until pork chops and potatoes are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: peach cake
directions: In a large bowl, add cake mix.
Use the juice from the peaches into the mix.
Mix and bake as directed on cake mix box.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Mix together beer and flour-refrigerate overnight in a covered container.
Dip dried-not wet, sliced onion rings into batter and fry in hot oil.

title: revell bars
directions: Melt on the stove or in microwave, add 1 cup nuts, 2 tsp. vanilla and set aside.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add margarine and sugar, beating well. Fold in nuts, coconut, flour and buttermilk.
Pour into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, celery, onion, pepper and pimentos.
Add sugar, vinegar and oil; stir.
Let stand 2 days, stirring occasionally.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 8 minutes.
Take off fire and add rest of ingredients.
Beat, pour into pan.
Cut into squares when firm. Good stored in tin cans.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple just to a boil (do not boil).
Add the Jell-O and let cool.
Add 2 cups buttermilk.
Chill slightly; then add the Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill well.

title: suzanne's hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well; store in a tightly covered container.*

title: carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cook sliced carrots in boiling salted water until tender, about 30 minutes.
Season with butter, salt and pepper.
May be served with white sauce.

title: milk tapioca
directions: Beat the eggs with a little of the milk (1/3 cup).
Mix in with the
rest of ingredients (except vanilla) and bring to a boil, stirring
constantly,
to	10 minutes.
Add vanilla after it thickens and it's off the stove.
Add pineapple.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken; shred. Flatten out biscuits. Put chicken and cheese (shredded) on biscuits. Roll up. Put cheese on top of roll-ups. Put in baking dish. Mix cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can milk. Pour over chicken roll-ups. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown. You can put left-over cheese in with soup mixture, then pour over roll-ups.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Line an average size casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch, with slices of pound cake.
Cover with layer of strawberries.
Repeat, then cover with the custard.

title: tangy rice
directions: Drain chiles.
Combine with sour cream, salt and pepper.
In a buttered casserole dish spread 1/3 of rice, layer with 1/2 of sour cream mixture and 1/2 of grated Jack cheese.
Repeat layers: rice, sour cream mix and Jack Cheese.
End with last 1/3 of rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake uncovered for 5 minutes more.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and beat well.
Add molasses and egg; mix well.
Add salt, spices and flour to the sugar mixture; stir until well mixed.
Chill dough for 3 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in tight container for freshness.
For each serving, use 2 teaspoonfuls of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.
Sure good!

title: creamy stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Wrap potatoes in foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise, and scoop out potato.
Combine scooped potato with butter, sour cream, chives and parslied garlic salt. Mash mixture with a fork until thoroughly mixed but still lumpy. Fill potato jackets with mixture.
Top with paprika and cheese. Place potatoes on a cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 20 people.

title: labaneh(syrian yogurt spread)
directions: Heat milk on low until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Add 4 tablespoons warm milk to yogurt and stir until smooth.
Stir yogurt into warm milk.
Pour into a plastic or glass container and wrap in a heavy blanket.
Store in a warm place until it thickens (about 6 hours), then refrigerate.

title: spiced watermelon rind
directions: Let melon stand overnight in salted water; drain.
Cover with fresh water and bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat until tender; drain.
Tie spices and lemon slices in cheesecloth.
Add sugar, water and vinegar; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add melon and cook until transparent.
