Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 pints.

title: sausage onion snack
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the following:

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: Scald the milk and pour over the oats.
Add the salt and shortening; blend in the molasses and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs, remaining water and mix well.
Stir in part of the flour, and the yeast and then the remaining flour.
Mix well and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into two loaves and bake 5 minutes at 400°; lower oven to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set lemon rind mixture aside. Remove broccoli leaves and cut off tough ends of stalks.
Discard. Wash broccoli roughly and cut into spears.
Arrange broccoli in a steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover and steam 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Arrange broccoli on a serving platter. Sprinkle with lemon rind mixture and lemon juice.

title: filled or sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375 for 12 minutes.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches 228°.
Add butter and pecans; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (235°).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture just begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: In saucepan place gelatin, sugar and half and half.
Mix over medium heat until hot, almost to a boil.
Mix in sour cream, pour into dish and let gel.
Mix together strawberry jello, 1 cup water, strawberries and juice.
Add enough water to make 2 cups total. Pour on top and chill.

title: mandarin orange fluff
directions: Drain juice from oranges.
Add water to make 2 cups liquid. Add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add and dissolve jello.
Cool and allow to partially set.
Whip the whipping cream.
Whip jello until fluffy.
Beat in sherbet.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add oranges.
Turn into mold and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: easy zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half crosswise; cut each piece into 6 sticks. Place zucchini in steaming rack.
Place rack over boiling water; cover and steam 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer zucchini to serving dish.
Combine butter and lemon juice; pour over zucchini and toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Place chicken, water and salt in pan.
Boil until chicken is tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Drain, reserving broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Cook garlic in butter for 2 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add cream of celery soup, 3/4 cup reserved broth, oregano and pepper.
Cook lasagne noodles in remaining broth, adding water, if needed.
Spoon a small amount of sauce into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Layer half each of noodles, sauce, chicken, Velveeta and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat procedure, reserving cheeses for later.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add cheeses.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: frosted  chocolate brownie supreme
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed

of an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar and beat well. Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well. Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 24 minutes or until a wooden pick in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack. Spread with Creamy Chocolate Frosting over cooled brownies and cut into squares. Yield: 24 servings.

title: company ham and noodles
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add ham and cook and stir until well heated.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low and gradually stir in sour cream. Add mushrooms. Cook and stir about 2 to 3 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all together with chopped parsley. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: peggy's hawaiian sweet potato balls
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes, butter, seasonings and brown sugar.
Drop 1/3 to 1/2 cup of sweet potato mixture onto waxed paper containing crushed cornflakes and roll into balls.
Place balls on pineapple on buttered cookie sheet.
Top with cherry. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rosalee's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a mixing bowl; add sugar and about 1/2 of the flour.
Beat thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and shortening; beat in gradually the remaining flour until smooth. Cover with a damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally and about 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed.
Return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Shape into rolls and brush tops with butter.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: vegetable stir-fry deluxe
directions: Slice meat very thin and marinate with soy sauce, salt, pepper and a tablespoon of Accent with sesame oil and fresh garlic or garlic powder.
Set aside.

title: triple rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
Stir occasionally.

title: ham-broccoli cups
directions: Place cheese and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat on medium until you have a thick cheese sauce.
Add the next 6 ingredients. Cook for 15 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil beets until tender and peel.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; simmer with the beets 20 minutes. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: cheese-pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and save juice. Mix pineapple chunks, measured juice, flour, sugar and grated cheese.
Top with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: fruit topped pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 Tbsp. syrup.
Beat cream cheese, dressing and syrup together until smooth.
Fold in banana, cherries and dates.
Arrange 1 pineapple slice on each of 8 lettuce leaves.
Top each slice with cheese-fruit mixture.
Top with cherry half.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Bake first 3 ingredients, mixed, in 13 x 10-inch dish in a 400° oven for 8 minutes; cool.
Soften cream cheese; blend with 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel bottom and refrigerate.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries. Let set 10 to 15 minutes until it starts to jell.
Spread over creamed mixture and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mud, dirt and snow cake
directions: You also need a punch bowl.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat egg whites in a bowl.
Add milk, flour and baking powder alternately in creamed butter and sugar.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease 2 loaf pans and pour in batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: mexican sugar cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and then gradually add to flour mixture.
Pinch off and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat
oven
at
Brown
meat	until
crumbly, draining off excess fat.
Add
onion
and pepper (if desired); set aside.
Combine eggs, 1
cup
corn and milk with cornbread mix. Stir just until
dry
ingredients
are
moistened.	Pour half of batter into greased
9-inch square pan.
Top with beef mixture, cheese slices and remaining 1 cup corn.
Pour remaining half of batter on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Butter a casserole and make 3 layers, 1/3 mushrooms, 1/3 bread, 1/3 butter and salt and pepper.
Pour wine over all after the last layer.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: crazy eggs
directions: Remove crust from bread, cube and place in bottom of greased, oblong Pyrex dish.
Melt Velveeta and butter, then pour over bread cubes.
Beat eggs and milk with salt, pepper and parsley to taste (about 1/2 teaspoon each).
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese; do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Stir in pudding mix, milk and lemonade concentrate.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat; spoon into pastry shell.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, water, oil and black pepper to a boil for the dressing.
Set aside.
Mix green pepper, celery, onion, corn, peas, green beans and pimentos together.
Pour dressing over vegetable mixture.
Stir once to mix.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Place chicken parts in a greased casserole.
Cover with canned mushroom soup (undiluted) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Chicken may be browned in oil with onion prior to the addition of soup, if preferred.
Serves 2.

title: marshmallow cream brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa over low heat.
In large bowl, stir eggs and sugar.
Pour chocolate mixture over egg and sugar mixture.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After baked, while hot, spread the marshmallow cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour, cocoa, butter, milk and vanilla and cook until thick.
Put into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites; when stiff, add sugar.
Beat a few seconds more.
Put on filling and bake at 450° until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together sugar and 3/4 cup peanut butter until crumbly and sprinkle 1/2 in the crust.
Mix pudding mix, milk and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Pour over crumbs in crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Butter and eggs should be at room temperature.
Take cream out of refrigerator 15 minutes before using.
Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla to the whipping cream, then alternate the flour and cream, adding both gradually.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together well, adding flour and oatmeal last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: pauline's taco soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and green chilies.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes on low.

title: vegetable fettucini carbonara
directions: Beat eggs with cream and set aside.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; remove and save.
Saute veggies and garlic in bacon fat until crisp and tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Cook 1 pound of fettucini; drain.
Toss with butter.
Add egg mixture and toss.
Add vegetables, bacon and cheese.
Season to taste and serve immediately.

title: potato soup for a crowd
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onions, parsley and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In another saucepan, melt butter and stir in a little flour.
Add in a small amount of liquid from potato mixture to form a paste.
Cool and stir in half and half and seasonings. When vegetables are cooked, mash and add milk mixture.
Stir constantly; do not boil.
Garnish with bacon.
Serve in bread bowls.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Add the butter, cream cheese, salt and pepper and whipping cream.
Mix with electric beater until smooth and fluffy.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and add uncooked noodles.
Shred chicken into pieces and return to pot.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes until noodles are tender.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 6 cups.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
In another big bowl, mix everything well.
Do not precook rice; mix in raw. Chop tomatoes and add with juice.
Mix very well.

title: zucchini and dill
directions: In saucepan, combine zucchini, onion, water, salt, bouillon and dill weed. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes until tender.
Do not drain.
Add butter, sugar and lemon juice. Remove from heat. Blend flour into sour cream. Stir about half of hot liquid into sour cream and return to pan. Cook until bubbly and thick.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Stir until it crumbles; drain and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Make well in center.
Combine milk, egg and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Place baking cups in muffin pan and spray cups.
Spoon batter into cups, filling 2/3's full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans.
Yield: 12 muffins.

title: caramel cuts
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add sugar, then rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Use 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour and salt. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix cake mix (except 1 cup), 1/2 cup melted margarine and egg. Press into slightly oiled 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, evaporated milk, eggs and pie spice.
Pour over cake mixture.
Mix the rest of cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Add all ingredients in order as listed:
lettuce, tomatoes, onion, chili beans, cheese, dressing, taco sauce, taco seasoning, hamburger and chips.
Toss lightly.
Add chips last, right before serving.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 cup liquid. Arrange, cut side up, in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add reserved liquid.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Top each peach half with 1 tablespoon cornflakes and a dot of butter.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: chocolate meringue topping
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy, then add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Beat until stiff peaks form and sprinkle on cocoa and fold in along with vanilla.
Spread this to the edge of the pie and brown in a hot oven.
Cool at least 30 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute the onions and garlic salt in the salad oil in a large Dutch oven pan until clear.
Add the rest of the ingredients; bring to a boil and then turn to simmer and simmer for 1 hour or more until of desired consistency.
Use as any recipe requests for spaghetti sauce.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add alternately with milk, flour, baking powder and cornmeal.
Spoon into paper liners in muffin pans.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Put flour into a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Make a depression in the center of dry ingredients and add milk.
Mix lightly with a fork to make a soft dough.
Toss and knead dough on lightly floured surface until smooth.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick, cut with floured biscuit cutter and bake in hot (450°) oven for about 12 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Combine sugar and melted margarine in bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in bananas.
Fold in flour and pecans. Do not beat.
Spoon into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In small frying pan, melt butter.
Add onion and broccoli and cook until tender.
Add rice.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Pour into baking dish sprayed with Pam and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Can be prepared ahead of time and baked just before serving.

title: crunch top banana loaf
directions: Crush cereal with rolling pin to make 1 cup crumbs.
Combine 1/4 cup cereal crumbs and 1/4 cup pecans, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon melted margarine; set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, banana and buttermilk; mix well. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Fold in remaining cereal crumbs and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely. Makes 1 loaf.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onion and tomatoes; drain. Parboil peppers in salted water for 3 minutes; drain.
Mix beef, tomato mixture and remaining ingredients in bowl.
Spoon into green peppers.
Arrange in baking pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water and salt in a small saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 25 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Add milk, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Set aside in a baking pan.
Pour hot water into baking pan to 1-inch depth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted 1-inch from edges comes back clean. Remove casserole dish from hot water to a wire rack.
Let cool.

title: blondies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Or may melt in microwave.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Spread batter evenly in a 9-inch square pan (for thinner cookies use a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan).
Butter pan well first. Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large stockpot, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside. In the same pot, saute onion in butter until soft. Stir in flour, salt and pepper; gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened. Gently stir in cooked vegetables. Add reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency. Yield: 8 servings.

title: corn vegetable casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Heat corn.
Add butter, eggs and sour cream.
Mix in the Jiffy mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with soda and spices. Cream butter, sugar and eggs; add chopped prunes and mix well. Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch square pan and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Do not overbake.
Best flavor after several days of storing.

title: anna bell's rum balls
directions: Crush wafers.
Add powdered sugar, nuts, cocoa, Karo and rum. Mix well.
Then roll in balls.
Roll formed balls in powdered sugar, then store in closed container.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese and chips.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Bread pork chops in flour and salt.
Fry on both sides in oil. Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Layer potato and onion slices in casserole dish.
Top with pork chops.
Dilute soup as directed on can and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix
cream
and flour, then butter.
Drop by tablespoon into small
greased
muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage cheese cloud
directions: Place 6 slices of buttered bread in greased dish.
Place 1/2 of cheese and meat over bread.
Add 6 more slices of bread, then rest of cheese and meat.
Beat eggs; add milk, onion and seasonings.
Pour over layered bread and meat.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat vigorously with spoon 1/2 minute; stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Sift together the flour and salt, cut in the shortening.
Beat the egg with 5 Tbsp. water, add to the flour and mix.
Use remaining water if necessary. Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: sour cream chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar;
beat
in egg, sour cream and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients and add chips.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces; place in the bottom of a large bowl.
Drain peas and add to top of lettuce.
Add sugar over peas. Slice onions in small round pieces and add to top of peas.
Add water chestnuts; then slice eggs and add to top of chestnuts. Next, sprinkle bacon bits over top of eggs.
Spread mayonnaise over the top to cover; sprinkle seasoning salt over top, not too heavy. Cover and let set overnight for full flavor.
Stir and serve.
A meal in itself.

title: microwave pumpkin cups
directions: Mix all together with rotary beater.
Pour into custard cups. Microwave on High until pumpkin starts to bubble.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In-5-quart saucepan over high heat, heat apple cider, cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, place orange and lemon slices in heat-safe 5-quart punch bowl; set aside.

title: broccoli 'n rice
directions: Heat broccoli.
Blend other ingredients together and mix with broccoli.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: grandma phyllis' birthday ice cream
directions: You also need an electric ice cream freezer.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour with sugar and baking powder. Make a well in center of mixture. Separately beat milk and egg whites until blended. Stir in yogurt. Pour into dry mixture. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in blueberries. Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling about 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for about 22 minutes.

title: tex mex
directions: Mix mashed avocados with lemon juice; set aside.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream; set aside.
On a plate or flat pan, layer as follows:
refried beans, thin layer of picante sauce, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, sliced black olives, shredded cheese and diced tomatoes on top.
Serve chilled with large nacho chips.

title: turkey ole
directions: Crumble turkey into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion and microwave for 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Combine soup, milk and salsa.
Add to cooked meat and microwave for 4 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of each cheese and microwave an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon onto tortillas; sprinkle with remaining cheese and fold tortillas. Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes; add to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and yeast to flour mixture.
Mix well. Pour out on board and roll to desired thickness.
Bake on greased pan at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed and drain.
Cut up vegetables.
Mix with pasta.
Add salad dressing, seasoning and Parmesan cheese. Serve warm or cold.

title: sandwich surprises
directions: Chop all ingredients.
Mix everything together.
Fill wiener buns and wrap in foil.
Bake in oven for about 10 minutes at 450°. Can be frozen before baked.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add dressing.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda; let stand. Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add bananas, salt and vanilla. Add buttermilk mix and flour alternately. Add nuts. Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Makes 1 large loaf. Freezes well or keep in refrigerator.

title: pineapple snack cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large heavy pot, brown the sausages.
Brown very well on all sides.
Peel garlic.
Peel and cut up onion.
Brown garlic and onion in fat from meat.
Put paste in pot.

title: avocado spread
directions: *Dice onions, using almost all of green stems.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 5 to 6 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices together and stir into pumpkin.
Add Milnot and eggs.
(Add nuts at this point, if being used.)
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for another 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: cornmeal pancake
directions: Combine buttermilk, egg and butter in a mixing bowl.
Stir briskly until mixture is smooth.
Stir together cornmeal, flour, salt and soda in a smaller bowl until well blended.
Stir into the buttermilk mixture only until moistened, leaving some lumps.
Heat griddle or skillet to medium hot.
Grease lightly and spoon out about 3 tablespoons of batter per pancake, spreading it with back of spoon.
Brown; then turn to brown other side.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and sugar.
Add water gradually until dough is stiff, but workable. Roll very thin on a floured board and fit into pan.
Trim and flute edges.
May wrap foil around edges to prevent edges browning too quickly.
Bake until lightly brown, according to instructions with filling.

title: italian chicken and vegetable grill
directions: Place chicken, zucchini and bell pepper in a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup of the salad dressing; turn to coat.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Gently remove stems and finely chop.
Drain caps.
In a 1-quart bowl combine butter, chopped stems, pepperoni, green pepper and garlic.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Mound mixture in mushroom caps.
Place in micro-safe dish.
Cover and cook on Medium for 4 minutes or until hot.

title: yeast rolls for a large crowd
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1 quart of warm water.
Add enough warm water to the flour to make dough.
Make out rolls and place in pans.
Let set at room temperature for an hour or overnight in fridge and let come to room temperature and bake.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot, baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes; leave skins intact to restuff.
Beat potatoes, cottage cheese, milk, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Spoon mixture back into skins.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°, until golden.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease well and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut; spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare the cake mix and pour over the nuts and coconut mixture.
In heavy saucepan, mix the cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Turn into serving tray.

title: unbridled sin!
directions: Layer 1/2 crushed macaroons or chocolate cookie wafers, mixed with one stick melted oleo, chocolate ice cream, 1/2 fudge sauce, more cookie mixture, 1/2 Heath bars (crushed), coffee ice cream, more fudge sauce and more crushed Heath bars.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
This works well in a spring-form pan.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Chop the broccoli in small pieces.
Chop green onions.
Cook bacon until crisp. Cool. Crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: almost cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together.
Cover and cook 1 hour on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 10 1/2-inch skillet.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain well.
Combine egg, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil.
Stir well.
Pour 1/2 cornbread in skillet.
Layer sausage and cheese.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Stir jello and water until clear; add pie filling.
Stir well; put into 9-inch square dish.

title: gravy baked venison
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add chopped onion. Coat steaks with flour & saute.
Remove all and place in baking dish. Pour mushroom soup over steak. Cover & bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Fry mushrooms and serve over steaks.

title: orange maple sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F.
Place sweet potatoes and garlic in medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 tsp salt and enough water to cover. Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until tender.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Let butter and cheese get soft, mix well.
Work together and add 3 cups Rice Krispies.
Make a ball about the size of a 50 cent piece.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fingers. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields approximately 75 cookies.

title: curried rice and shrimp
directions: Heat 1/2 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and curry powder and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove shrimp and set aside.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Boil noodles. Combine everything into a crock-pot and heat on low 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except eggs) together.
Halve eggs and scoop out yolks.
Mix yolks with other ingredients.
Stuff whites and refrigerate.
Garnish with paprika or black olives.

title: rich chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Heat peanut butter and butter or margarine together until melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour and stir just until blended.
Spread batter into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: tommy's forget-me-not(roma flae thomas hollopeter (1910 - 1992))
directions: In small amount of oil saute the celery and onion until soft. Add ground chuck, brown and drain.
Add can of spaghetti and peas; mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole and bake uncovered in a 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until hot.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Thaw spinach or broccoli, press, dry and chop.
Set aside. Thaw potatoes, separate and mix with half the salt and half the cheese.
Press over the bottom and the sides of a 9-inch pie pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over dates and cool.
Add orange peel and juice; stir in egg.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture and stir until mixed.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour a loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: mango lime mousse with raspberry sauce
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over lime juice in a small saucepan and allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Peel mangoes and cut fruit off seed.
In a bowl, mash mangoes together with cream until smooth.
Over low heat, melt gelatin in lime juice.
Add to mango mixture.
Stir and place in bowl in refrigerator.
(You can freeze.)
On day you are going to serve, place thawed package of raspberries in blender with 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/4 cup of Chambord.
Blend, then put mixture through sieve to eliminate seed.
Pour over mousse when ready to serve.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Saute green onion, bell pepper and carrots in cooking oil until wilted.
Add cabbage, salt and pepper.
Fry for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: anita's blend of the bayou
directions: Melt cream cheese and 1 stick oleo in microwave.
Saute shrimp and vegetables in 1 stick of oleo.
Add to first mixture.
Add golden mushroom soup, seasoning and rice; mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese and cracker meal or crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly hot. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: egg and avocado
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve as a spread or appetizer.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 13 x 9 pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Beat in cream cheese.
Spread pie filling over cake, add pudding mixture then top with cool whip.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Then cream shortening and sugar.
Then add molasses and egg.
Mix.
Then add baking powder, flour, clove, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well, then roll into balls and then roll into sugar.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: gotto speise
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Whip the cream until stiff.

In a glass dish, layer the crumb mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon and brandy. Top with whipped cream. Repeat layers until you have 6 layers, the final being cream. Top with grated chocolate. Chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and make as any other cake.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Into 1 part, put 1 teaspoon each of cinnamon and allspice, raisins and nuts.
Bake this part and other part in 2 layers each at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp tempura
directions: Shell shrimp.
Slit the back and open butterfly fashion. Devein and wash thoroughly.
Dry. Set aside in a cool place.

title: russian tea
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place 2 rounded tablespoons of mix in each cup; fill with boiling water. Stir well.
Makes 32 servings.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, oleo, eggs and syrup. Beat up good until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool completely in pan. Spread Mint Cream Center on cake.
Cover and chill.
Pour Chocolate Topping over chilled dessert. Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: seaside salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: herbed garlic bread
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the butter, thyme, rosemary, oregano and basil.
Heat over low heat until the butter is melted. Slice the bread and generously brush the butter mixture on each slice.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Bake in a 475° oven or under the broiler until browned.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into hot oil (1 teaspoon at a time).
Cook until lightly golden brown.
Drain well.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Bake in 2 round pans.
Poke holes in cake with a knife while it is still warm (lots of holes).
Mix cherry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water; pour this over 1 layer.
Mix lime Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and pour over other layer.
Chill in pans for at least 4 hours.
Place one layer on cake plate and cover with Cool Whip, then put the other layer on top and cover it with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries. Keep cake refrigerated.

title: oyster and spinach soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender; add oysters which have been halved or chopped coarsely.
Cook until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Blend in flour; cook until bubbly. Gradually add half and half and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in broth and spinach; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add salt and pepper.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 9 hours.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in the 2 tablespoons butter. In saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter. Stir in sour cream and soup until blended. Place meat mixture and soup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add carrots and then potatoes. Top with cheese and then the corn flakes. Sprinkle on paprika and parsley to taste. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6-8.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook broth, celery and onion for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and veggies.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add the soup and cheese.
Heat on medium low until the cheese melts, taking care not to scorch the soup.

title: drip beef on buns
directions: Remove excess fat; the leaner, the better. Place in Dutch oven or crock-pot. Put in seasonings; barely cover with water and simmer 8 to 10 hours covered in slow oven. When done, lift meat to platter; shred with fork and return to pot. Serve on warm buns. Serves 12.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil in microwave about 1 minute. In large bowl, add spices and mix. Pour crackers into bowl and mix until oil is absorbed. These are great with chili.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cream soup and cream cheese on stove until melted.
Mix in shrimp, onion and mayonnaise.
Add gelatine (and hot sauce to taste, if desired).
Pour in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Place roast on rack in oven roasting pan.
Roast in 325° oven, allowing 30 minutes per pound.
Roast will be rare.
Cool and slice very thin.
To drippings in pan, add water and 1 bouillon cube for each cup of water used.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Add thinly sliced beef and marinate in gravy in refrigerator overnight.
Serve warm on Italian bread.

title: my best pound cake
directions: Cream well the butter; gradually add sugar and blend well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition, then add flour alternately with whipping cream.
Blend well after each addition.
Then add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
If cake starts to get too brown, last 30 minutes cover with foil.
Remove foil last 5 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on wax paper.

title: vanilla giffolds
directions: Mix together well.
Bake while warm.
Roll in extra powdered sugar.
Shape dough into half moons.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon bread(cornbread souffle)
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until very thick. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Allow to cool.
Let mix become cold and stiff (if time permits).
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes (if time permits).
Pour into well-greased casserole pan or iron skillet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Serve immediately with lots of butter.
(The souffle will fall.)

title: herring bits and sour cream
directions: Mix together and pour on herring.
Carefully turn with fork to coat all pieces evenly.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: nachos
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and salsa.
Heat and stir.
Pour over chips and top with other ingredients.

title: lemon butter snowbars
directions: Pat into ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add sugar and salt, stirring until blended.
Add milk and vanilla to egg mixture; stir well.
Pour into glasses.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and softened margarine together until crumbly.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix molasses, baking soda and water together and add to flour mixture.
Mix well and pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old time sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix dry ingredients with first mixture.
Then add 3 cups of flour, a little at a time, until mixture is very stiff.
Drop spoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Dampen finger and pat out each cookie.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen big cookies.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in pieces.
Mix with onions, 1 can tomato sauce, rice, ground beef, salt and pepper in large pan.
Pack in casserole and pour last can of sauce and Tabasco sauce on top plus 1/2 can water.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours after it starts to bubble or until rice in the center is cooked.
Place in oven on pizza pan.
It will cook over.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 cup uncooked rice on bottom of pan and spread out.
Place chicken on top of rice; add 2 cups water, then add Lipton soup mix.
Do not stir.
Put pats of butter on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn and cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain on paper towel.
Add water, sugar and salt to bacon drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage and corn.
Cover; cook quickly just until tender, about 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika; garnish with crisp bacon, crumbled.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Have baked pie crust prepared.
Set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium saucepan blend sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups warm water, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Cool partially.
In a small bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir egg yolks in small amounts into the warm cornstarch sauce.
Return to heat and cook, stirring, until thickens.
Do not boil.

title: taco bake dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Put crushed Doritos chips on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon hamburger over chips.
Heat soup and milk until smooth; spoon over meat.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, etc.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Dissolve gelatine in cold water. In blender, combine mayonnaise, onion, cottage cheese, cucumber, Tabasco sauce, garlic and almonds. Blend well, then add Jell-O and gelatine. Blend again. Pour into a mold and chill overnight.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Add sugar and eggs to melted butter, then add flour and baking soda.
Let stand until firm, then drop by 1/4 teaspoon.
Beat eggs and brush on top of cookies; add nuts to top of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on a 13 x 9-inch pan for approximately 15 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: pretzel-pineapple salad
directions: Mix 1/3 cup sugar and pretzels into melted margarine.
Put in flat dish and bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple and 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip. Mix well.
Spread over pretzel crust in dish.
Top with second 8 ounces of Cool Whip.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Grate Velveeta and Cheddar cheese.
Mix these ingredients with the mayonnaise (do not use salad dressing). Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add oil and stir well. Add 1 egg
at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in carrots. Use 3
(8-inch)
greased
and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Spread nuts.
Bake 10 minutes.
In medium saucepan, bring sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves and salt to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Remove nuts to waxed paper. Separate.
Let dry.
Keep in cool, dry place.

title: copper penny relish
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut into round slices.
Cover with salt water and boil until just tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots and refrigerate. Keeps well in refrigerator and is better the longer it sets. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 pints and is also good mixed into green salads.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, granulated sugar, lemon juice and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust. Return to oven and bake at 350° for 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: calumet baking powder corn bread
directions: Pour boiling water over corn meal and let stand until cool. Sift flour together with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light and add them to corn meal, then add milk, flour and melted butter.
Beat until the batter is smooth.
Pour into a shallow, well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 generous servings.

title: chiquita chicken
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add soups.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add chicken broth and chilies.
Place a layer of tortilla strips on the bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour some sauce on that and add a layer of chicken.
Repeat, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caldillo (cal-di-o)(a traditional northern mexican dish; a soup)
directions: Cook meat until done.
Put your garlic, onion and bouillon cubes and seasoning.
Also green chili.
Cook potatoes by themselves, then add to meat and seasonings.

title: meat gravy
directions: Remove meat from pan.
Strain drippings and remove fat except for 1 to 2 tablespoons.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Blend into them flour with wire whisk until flour has thickened and until mixture is well combined and smooth.
Continue to cook slowly and stir constantly while adding degreased pan juices and whatever liquid you choose to make 1 cup.
Add salt, pepper and minced herbs.
Add a few drops of coloring.
Cook until thickened. Makes 1 cup.
(Can be doubled.)

title: special meatballs(a great appetizer!)
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together; shape into small balls and brown in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese-style shrimp in pastry shells
directions: Mix chicken broth with teriyaki sauce and cornstarch. In a large skillet, heat oil over high heat. Add snow peas and onions; stir-fry until almost tender-crisp. Add shrimp and stir in chicken broth mixture; cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and just comes to a boil and shrimp are tender.

title: quick egg custard
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Thin crust will form on bottom.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla thoroughly.
Form into small, slightly flattened balls.
Chill for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip each ball in chocolate, leaving an uncovered light spot to resemble a buckeye.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper. Brown on all sides in 2 tablespoons oil. Add onion and garlic. Brown lightly. Pour off excess oil. Add 1 jar Ragu Italian sauce. Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Chop leeks, onion and celery.
In pan, melt butter and add leeks, onion and celery.
Stir well until well covered with butter.
Add chicken stock, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Puree in food processor or blender.
It will be thick.
Add to soup the hot cream and stir well.
Serve at once. May add chives or parsley to top of soup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: liver (as we like it)
directions: Grind liver or
put in blender.
(Don't overload blender.) I put egg, onion, pepper
and
seasonings in, after liver.
Add flour.
Place by tablespoons in
hot
greased skillet.
Serve with catsup or barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: goody bars
directions: Mix margarine, German chocolate cake mix and one egg and press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Mix confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese and pour over the pressed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cut into bars.

title: sauce d'arachide(peanut butter sauce over rice)
directions: Brown beef in 2 tablespoons oil along with onion and garlic. Add enough water for cooking the beef (like beef stew).
Continue adding the rest of the ingredients except the peanut butter.
Add it the last 20 minutes, stirring to make sure it dissolves. Cooking time is approximately 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate filled cupcakes
directions: Combine cheese, egg, 1/2 C sugar, 1/8 tsp salt in a mixing bowl, beat well.
Stir in in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Combine in another bowl flour, 1 C sugar, cocoa, soda, and 1 tsp salt. Sift Together.
Bake in muffin tins until done.

title: chocolate refrigerator roll
directions: Stir vanilla extract into whipped cream or frozen whipped topping; spread 1 1/2 to 2 cups on wafers.
Put wafers together in stacks of 4 or 5.
On serving platter, stand stacks on edge to make one roll; frost with remaining whipped cream or topping. Chill 4 to 6 hours; if desired, garnish with chocolate curls.
To serve, slice diagonally at 45° angle.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep popcorn warm in a 250° oven.
In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the next 4 ingredients for 5 minutes, stirring often. Remove from burner and add the soda (it will foam up).
Mix and pour quickly over popcorn, coating well.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Make into smal balls and bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cube all the meats and cheeses, enough to make 2 cups total. Divide thawed dough in 2 parts.
Roll out on floured surface. Butter each half; sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.
Spread half of cheese and meat mixture on each piece of dough.
Roll up like jelly roll (put seam on bottom).
Let rise until double and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Rub lightly with soft margarine when hot from oven.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough to top, center of chicken mixture, twist slightly and seal edges. Brush tops with reserved 1 tablespoon margarine.
Dip in croutons crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes four sandwiches.
Serve with sauce or gravy. These take a little time, but are really good.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Blend all (in processor or blender). Bake until lightly brown at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Melba rounds.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, melted margarine and chopped pecans and pat into bottom of pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine jello with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Put 1/2 mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Set until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Put remaining mixture on top.
Refrigerate until set or next day. Serve on lettuce leaf or as a dessert.

title: best chocolate pudding
directions: Hint:
Put milk and eggs in blender; it makes creamier pudding.

title: sausage casserole(essie's)
directions: Fry sausage in a large pan until browned and cooked through. Remove with a slotted spoon. Crumble when cooled. Set aside. Saute peppers, celery and onions in pan with sausage juices until soft and lightly brown; set aside. In a large pot, bring water to a boil. Add soup mix and rice. Reduce to a slow simmer and cook uncovered until rice is done and liquid has reduced. Remove soup mixture from heat; add sausage, vegetables, chicken soup and soy sauce. Pour into two 9 x 13 pans and top with almonds. Bake in a preheated 350° oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: sugarless pumpkin pie
directions: Roll pastry on floured surface, ease into pan and flute the edges.
Beat pumpkin, milk and eggs, in medium bowl.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated over 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake until knife comes out clean when tested in middle, about 40 minutes.

title: copper coin salad
directions: Drain and cool cooked carrots in ice cubes for 30 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over cooled carrots. Refrigerate.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Add the mayonnaise to the consistency you want.
Real good and easy.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly. Add the milk, oil, vanilla and egg whites.
Mix thoroughly with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn mixer to low. Slowly add 1 cup of boiling, strong black coffee.
Beat slowly until well blended.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees; cut biscuits into fourths. Place sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag. Add biscuit pieces a few at at time, and shake to coat. Place pieces in a greased tube pan until all are used. Sprinkle layers with pecans, raisins or coconut if desired. Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil in a saucepan, and pour over top of biscuits. Bake for 45 minutes. Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan. Turn topside up toss serve.

title: cracker salad
directions: Break up crackers.
Mix tomato, onion, eggs and mayonnaise. Add crackers last, just before serving.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool and add 3 cups diced apples, 1/2 cup chopped celery and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: soy and hot mustard dipping sauce
directions: Mix water and mustard to form a paste.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add soy sauce and stir well.

title: woco - 'em cheese fries
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°. Spread the French fries evenly on a large rimmed baking sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Mound the cooked French fries on a serving platter and top with the melted cheese, salsa and bacon bits. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until done.
When cool, invert on plate and prick with fork.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown meat. Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in applesauce, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir just to moisten.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, dip in melted butter.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend the 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add the pineapple, juice and all.
Cook, stirring until the mixture is thick and clear.
Cool.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cool.
Combine butter, sugar, egg, salt and vanilla; add to date mixture.
Combine nuts and flour with other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes for small pan, or 60 to 70 minutes in large pan.

title: french bread garlic-cheese loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With sharp knife, make 13 evenly spaced deep vertical slits in loaf of bread, being careful not to slice all the way through.
Set aside.
In blender, process cottage cheese until smooth.
Add parsley, Parmesan cheese, onion, garlic and pepper.
Process until parsley and garlic are minced.
Press bread open between slices.
With small spatula, spread cheese mixture on surface.
Bake 8 minutes, or until hot and crispy. Serve hot.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Drain shrimp, saving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Add gelatin to the 1/4 cup of liquid and let soak. Soften cream cheese; heat tomato soup.
Slowly pour hot tomato soup into cream cheese and blend with mixer.
Stir gelatin mix and add to cream cheese mixture.
Let cool, then add mayonnaise and all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate. Allow mold to gel before serving.
Enjoy with friends!

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef cubes in large kettle.
Drain off excess fat.
Add beef base, water, onion, celery, thyme and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender and meat is cooked, about 1 hour.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, salt, pepper and frozen vegetables.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until frozen vegetables are tender.
Makes 16 (1-cup) servings.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° or until middle is set.

title: lucy ann's bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and garlic in a bowl.
Sprinkle salt over all. Cover with cracked ice.
Mix by hand.
Let stand at least 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat the remaining ingredients. Put in pot. Add drained vegetables (minced garlic). Heat to boiling.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 6 or 7 pints.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: savory succotash
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish, except Cheese Nips and margarine.
Crush the Cheese Nips; mix with the margarine.
Put crumb mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in dish on top of butter (don't mix).
Add fruit or berries.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients except for flour and egg.
Add flour to form stiff dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Shape; roll into a rope. Place on greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Brush each pretzel with beaten egg.
Put coarse salt (Crazy Jane's) on each pretzel.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in medium saucepan. Combine in large bowl the oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil. Shut off. Mix dry ingredients with wet and then put on foil. Let cool.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Parboil dried beans for 45 minutes, covered; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook 1 hour in pressure cooker after stopper starts to jiggle.
Or bake in covered oven-proof pot for 6 to 8 hours at 250°.
Do not add all the water at once, but add water as needed, to keep beans moist.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Mix oil, milk and egg together and add this mixture to the flour mixture and mix well.
Pour out on lightly floured board and knead, 5 to 7 minutes.
Let dough rise on board for 20 minutes. Cut into desired shapes; place in greased muffin pans and brush top of rolls with margarine.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 3 dozen rolls.

title: fruit cups
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Chop the fruit.
Hand mix fruit with remaining ingredients.
Fill 3 lightly oiled (I spray with Pam) mini muffin tins.
Bake for approximately 35 minutes.
Don't let them get too brown.
Remove from heat; let them cool about 10 minutes before removing from tins.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix in 2 layers (split to make 4) or oblong layer.
Split into layers when cooled.
Mix 2 cups of sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Set aside 1 cup of the mixture.
Put remaining mixture between layers.

title: broccoli beef
directions: Marinate beef with soy sauce, sesame oil and cooking wine. Heat 5 tablespoons of peanut oil in a preheated wok.
Quickly stir-fry beef until meat changes color. Pull beef up the side of the wok to stop it from cooking.

title: texas breakfast rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Split chilies and discard seeds.
Arrange chilies on bottom of baking dish and top with combined cheeses.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and biscuit mix.
Blend well and pour over cheese. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown at edges. Serve with salsa.
Salt to taste.

title: crunch cocoa cookies
directions: Stir well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 dozen.

title: dina's hot and spicy tuna
directions: Put the tomato sauce in pan; mix the tomato sauce with garlic and hot sauce.
Then add butter or margarine and salt.
Now, add the tuna in the frying pan.
Cook for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until wilted.
Add cream of mushroom soup and stir.
Add egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a bowl suitable for mixing and pour the cooked sauce over the crabmeat.
Blend well and transfer into lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Serves 6.

title: elegant squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam squash, carrots and onion until tender.
Drain in a colander, mashing with the back of a spoon to remove the excess water.
Meanwhile, melt 1/4 cup margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute, then gradually add the milk and stir one more minute.
Add the salt, pepper and nutmeg and remove from heat.
Add sour cream and pimentos to the squash mixture and fold into the skillet mixture.
Melt the remaining 1/4 cup margarine and toss with the herb stuffing mix.
Put half this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spoon the squash mixture over the top and top with remaining half of the herb stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Serves 12.
Freezes well when wrapped in foil.

title: hot mustard
directions: Beat all together. Let stand overnight in China bowl. Put in jars. Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together over low heat.
In a bowl, mix sugar and flour.
Pour margarine and peanut butter into dry ingredients and mix well by hand.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 of the soup with remaining ingredients, except water.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water.
Spoon over patties. Bake 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend together eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix in pumpkin and water. Then add all dry ingredients.
This may be done with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: mom's light fruitcake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar until fluffy, adding eggs, flour and lemon extract.
Fold in flour coated fruits and nuts. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Put pan of water in oven also.
Cool in pans, then remove and wrap in hot damp towel (can soak with rum).
After towel has cooled, remove, wrap and put in fridge.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat well first 3 ingredients and spread on platter.
Spread taco sauce on top of the first mixture.
Cut up fine onions, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes and layer of lettuce.
Chopped black olives on top.
Serve with taco, wheat or nacho crackers or chips.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add eggs, dates and walnuts. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-in pan for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat three minutes. Cool.
Add powdered sugar and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: fancy fried rice
directions: Pour eggs into a nonstick skillet sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Cook until set in one large pancake. Remove from pan. Cool and cut into thin strips and reserve. Heat 1 teaspoon liquid Butter Buds in pan, adding garlic, celery, green pepper, green onion (not tops) and carrot. Brown, stirring constantly, for about 2 minutes. Add the second teaspoon of Butter Buds, adding cooked rice. Stir constantly until heated through and slightly browned. Stir in bean sprouts.
Mix together soy sauce, lemon juice, sherry and ginger and pour over all. Place on serving dish and sprinkle egg strips and tops of green onions. Serves 4.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook water and sugar to soft ball stage.
Take off heat and add other ingredients except pecans.
Pour syrup over the pecans until each pecan is glazed.
Spread on a cookie sheet.

title: hot viking punch
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve hot or chill over ice cubes.

title: ranch style chicken or pheasant
directions: Simmer chicken or pheasant until tender.
Bone it.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients well by mixer.
Spread on 6 whole English muffins, split! Cut into six wedges.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
May be frozen for weeks.
Broil them until they puff up (on cookie sheet) and are bubbly and slightly golden brown.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Remove.
Heat oysters in remaining butter until edges curl.
Combine all ingredients including oyster liquid.
Season to taste.

title: scalloped broccoli("a terrific company casserole")
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Put 1/2 of broccoli in casserole.
Spread 1/2 can of mushroom soup over broccoli.
Sprinkle grated American cheese over soup.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Repeat, using rest of broccoli soup and cheese.
Be sure potato chips are on top.
Bake in a covered dish in oven at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook
in
double boiler until dissolved. Beat with hand beater or low mixer until thick.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water; drain while still hot.
Stir in grated cheese.
Set aside.
Brown meat and onion in margarine. Stir in soup and milk.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer cheese mixture and meat mixture; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix crumbled cornbread with melted butter.
Spread half of cornbread mixture in casserole.
Combine all other ingredients and place in casserole.
Cover with remaining cornbread.
Make at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine soup, soup mix and milk, stirring until smooth; set aside 1/2 cup.
Spoon remainder of soup mixture evenly over rice.
Top with chicken, meaty side up; spoon remaining 1/2 cup soup mixture over chicken.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pot roast with dill pickles
directions: Brown the roast well in the oil.
Place the meat in a covered casserole, adding everything but the sour cream.
Simmer for about 2 hours, or until meat is very tender.
Add the sour cream; simmer for 1/4 hour more.
Slice and serve with the rich sauce on the top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and sour cream together by hand.
Put 1/2 batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon, raisins and nuts together.
Sprinkle over cake and swirl with a knife.
Pour remaining batter on top and swirl again.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Glaze cake while hot.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and mix together.
In a large glass dish, layer ingredients in order given and then sprinkle cheese over top.

title: chow chow
directions: Heat to boiling.
Add the well drained vegetables and cook slowly
until tender (about 1/2 hour).
Pack in hot pint jars. Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath (canner) for 10 minutes.

title: cold noodles and spicy sauce
directions: In a kettle or large saucepan, bring about 6 cups of water to a boil and add the chicken breast. Do not add salt.
Return to a boil and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook, or the meat will be dry.
Remove the chicken breast, but leave the water in the kettle.
Bring the water to a boil again.
Do not add salt. Add the noodles and cook, occasionally stirring, until they are tender, 7 minutes or less.
Drain in a colander and run under cold water until the strands are separated and thoroughly chilled. Drain.
Sprinkle with the teaspoon of sesame oil and toss to coat. Set aside.

title: company breakfast
directions: Remove bread crusts.
Arrange
slices
in
bottom of large baking pan.
Cover
with
cheese, ham and rest of bread. Mix rest of ingredients
together
and
pour over layered mixture.
Cover. Let stand
1 hour or overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 hour
until
brown and puffy.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place in 350° oven.
Chop onion and grate cheese.
Combine corn meal, soda, salt, oil, milk and eggs (beaten).
Add cream-style corn and mix thoroughly.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo; add eggs and mix well with remaining ingredients. Bake in buttered casserole dish 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9-inch pie shell.

title: cream of cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage, celery, potato and onion in water until tender. Put in blender container; cover.
Run on high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and run on low speed for 15 seconds, until mixed.
Reheat to serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: tortilla strips
directions: Mix cream cheese, green chilies, black olives and garlic powder.
Spread on flour tortillas and stack two together.
Fold over like a fried pie.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Cut before serving.
Make strips and dip in picante sauce.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package, drain.
Meanwhile cook and stir remaining ingredients, except parsley, in medium saucepan until hot; pour sauce over hot pasta and toss to coat well.
Serve with parsley and additional grated Locatelli (or Parmesan) cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brickle blend brownies
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in brickle.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven in a 11 x 7-inch Pyrex.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Saute onions and garlic in the oil from the artichokes.
Beat the eggs; add the cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Blend in chopped artichokes, parsley, cheese and onions.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Test doneness with a knife in center of Frittata; center should be firm and the knife clean.

title: layered dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix by hand butter, flour and pecans.
Press into 9 X 13 baking dish and bake 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add a drop or two of milk, if needed.
Spread over cooked crust.
Mix together instant pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese.
Top with softened Cool Whip.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce up and spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread rest of ingredients, one at a time, over lettuce.

title: lava dessert
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and baking powder; set aside.
Beat together butter, sugars, vanilla and almond.
Add eggs one at a time, beating very slowly.
Pour in dry ingredients and mix.
Put in custard cups that have been sprayed with butter PAM.
Fill only 3/4 full and drop chocolate chips on top.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes only.
They will sink in the middle when they cool which gives a place to put a scoop of ice cream with caramel and nuts.
The bottom of the cake should be a bit gooey which is why it is called lava dessert.

title: special bars
directions: Measure cereal and place in large bowl.
Measure corn syrup into medium size pan on medium heat.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add peanut butter until melted.
Add raisins; stir and then cool.
Pour over cereal and stir.
Put into 13
x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Push down with hands and let sit 20 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: crustless quiche
directions: In a greased 10-inch quiche pan, spread cheese, then bacon and then mushrooms.
In blender, mix rest of ingredients and pour over ingredients in quiche pan.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° gas oven. Let stand 4 minutes before serving.

title: unique chocolate cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients (first 6).
Put remaining ingredients in a bowl and beat 3 minutes.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
A 9 x 12-inch pan may be used.
The following glaze may be drizzled over cake while warm.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles by directions on box.
Brown beef; pour off grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly until bouillon cube is dissolved.
Mix drained noodles.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish stew
directions: Cut lamb into 1 1/2 inch cubes.
Peel and slice onions and potatoes in 1/8-inch thickness.
Put in the bottom of a heavy pan a layer of potatoes, a layer of meat and a few slices of onion. Repeat this twice, ending with potatoes on top.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Add to the pot, one bay leaf and pour over the layers 2 cups of water and the 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer gently about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Shake pot periodically to keep potatoes from sticking. When done, all the moisture should have been absorbed by the potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Simmer hen until tender; remove and add noodles to broth. Cook until tender.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Mix together with noodles, soup and chicken which has been taken from bone and cut up.
Add pimento and enough chicken broth to make it very moist.
Put into baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and is lightly brown on top.
Good to fix ahead of time and freeze.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients until very well mixed. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or golden brown.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Microwave both packages of morsels 3 to 4 minutes in large glass container on Medium power.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons into candy cup petit fours cases.
Chill until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cherry jello, brown sugar and salt with 1 cup of hot water.
Let dissolve well and add 1 cup of 7-Up.
Let jell in the refrigerator and then add the can of cranberry sauce.
Mix well and add all the other ingredients.
Serve over lettuce, if you like.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together and pour into 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle a little powdered sugar on top.

title: tuna log
directions: Drain tuna.
Cream tuna and cream cheese together.
Add onion salt, garlic salt and Worcestershire.
Roll into log.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Chill and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
Saute stems and onions in butter until onions are tender.
Combine onion mixture with remaining ingredients.
Spoon into mushroom cups.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot antipasto
directions: *Bring water to a boil and drop hearts in; drain, cool and cut up.

title: mini sub sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, spread roll with mayonnaise; fill with remaining ingredients.
Yields 6 sandwiches.
Preparation time 20 minutes.

title: peas and celery
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add celery and next 4 ingredients.
Stir in savory, if desired.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, 5 to 7 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender. Add peas and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: pumpkin cream cheese muffins
directions: Put 2 eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin in mixing bowl.
Beat.
Mix dry ingredients separately and mix.
Add pumpkin mixture all at once and mix only until just moistened.
Divide among 24 muffin cups and keep remainder for top.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and Karo syrup in heavy 3-quart pan and cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Add pecan halves and drop by tablespoons onto wax paper. When firm, store in closed container.
You've never tasted candy until you've had a pecan praline.
They are sinfully delicious and rich and this recipe is more sinful than most.
Enjoy!

title: squash and stuffing casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of lightly salted water in saucepan until squash is tender; drain.
Add soup, carrots, milk, eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Mix butter and stuffing mix in small bowl; reserve 1/2 cup mixture.
Add remaining stuffing mixture to squash; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: sour cream cutout cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Blend thoroughly margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix in flour mixture.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Bisquick and sugar in bowl.
Beat egg, milk and extract together in another bowl, then stir into Bisquick mixture.

title: date pudding
directions: Soak dates in the soda and hot water mixture.
Mix rest of ingredients; it will make a thin batter; then add dates and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: avocado dip
directions: Lightly mash avocados.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving with chips or crackers.

title: pear, raspberry and rhubarb crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir raspberries, rhubarb, pears, honey, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: apri-curry chicken
directions: In glass baking dish, combine ingredients with half teaspoon salt.
Add chicken.
Turn to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 to 5 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Remove onion from butter and pour in cracker crumbs.
Add onion to the beans, grated cheese and soup.
Mix and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
