title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Mix all ingredients except chips in a crock-pot or double boiler.
Slow cook until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and put on low heat.
Cook until the consistency of apple butter.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch and milk in a glass bowl; mix until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Microwave (High), uncovered, for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Mix in vanilla.
Cool.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and dill in butter for 15 minutes until soft.
Add flour and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in broth and simmer for 20 minutes and add cream.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding crab meat last.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Place on tray and put in freezer for 45 minutes.
Take out and cut in 4ths.
Put in freezer bag for later use when unexpected guests arrive.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°. Makes 24 Puffs.

title: grandma case's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all together and fold into beaten egg whites.
Put into single pie crust and bake until brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cut cheese in cubes.
Stir tomato soup and cheese together over low flame until blended.
Remove from fire.
Dissolve gelatine in water.
Add mixture to soup mixture in large bowl. Mix together.
Refrigerate two hours.
After 2 hours, add celery, onion and shrimp to soup mixture.
Add mayo.
Mix well.
Put in mold.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown chops.
Put sliced potatoes in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and water; pour mixture over.
Put browned chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Season the meat with the salt and pepper and place in a large bowl.
Bring the vinegar and water to a boil and add the garlic, onion, bay leaf, peppercorns, sugar and cloves.
Pour the marinade over the beef, cover and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Remove the meat and dry thoroughly with paper towels.
Reserve the marinade.
Drench the meat with flour.
In a heavy kettle, heat the bacon drippings; add the meat and brown on all sides.
Add 2 cups of the marinade, cover tightly and simmer gently until the meat is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove the meat to a warm platter and keep hot.
Thicken the gravy with a little flour mixed with water. Stir in the sour cream and serve over sliced meat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza fondue
directions: In a heavy saucepan, brown onion and beef.
Drain off fat. Stir in pizza sauce, cornstarch, oregano and garlic powder.
Mix well. Add 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Stir until the cheese melts.

title: pretty-as-a-picture pudding pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and orange rind.
Put in baked pie shell.
Arrange fruit on top.
Brush with melted apple jelly to glaze.

title: chicken breast gourmet
directions: Season chicken and flatten slightly between cling free, using rolling pin.
Place ham and cheese on each breast.
Fold chicken over into sandwich.
Secure with toothpick.
Grease ovenproof dish with melted butter.
Put in breast.
Arrange tomatoes and mushrooms around chicken and add dab of butter.
Place dish in center of oven.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
After 15 minutes, baste chicken.

title: crab salad
directions: Butter bread and break it up. Add onion and egg. Blend and refrigerate overnight. Add other ingredients and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Soften oleo, then whip with electric mixer.
Add salt, garlic salt and red pepper.
Mix well.
Add flour a little at a time and mix well after each time.
Then add cheese and Rice Krispies. Roll in 1/2-inch balls, flatten with fork.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400°.
Some ovens about 6 minutes.
Store in tin.

title: cabbage coleslaw
directions: Heat together sugar, cider vinegar, water and spices.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir in 5 tablespoons oil. This will keep 2 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: grandpa hawley's molasses cookies
directions: Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Grease hands with margarine.
Roll into 1-inch diameter balls and place on cookie sheet, then flatten to 1/2-inch by pressing down.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: orange delight(a drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed until mixture is frothy and well blended.
Pour into glasses at once.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries, unpeeled apples and orange together.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Using 1 1/2 cups water per each box of Jell-O, mix as per instructions on box.
Mix with fruit and refrigerate.
Serves many.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, cinnamon and soda.
Mix with persimmon puree, white and brown sugars, eggs, vanilla, evaporated milk and melted margarine.

title: cheese roll
directions: Sprinkle paprika
on
wax paper and roll mixture to the size of a
Ritz cracker.
Then roll in paprika until all sides are covered.
Wrap
in wax paper and store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together except blueberries.
Stir until well blended.
Fold in drained blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together until totally blended.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Boil chicken wings until done; drain, then put wings in long glass pan.
Sprinkle package of Ranch salad dressing over all chicken.
In a bowl, mix 1/2 cup Texas Pete, 1 cup butter and 6 tablespoons of vinegar.
Pour over all wings.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except spareribs; heat to boiling. Pour sauce over spare ribs.
Chill overnight if desired.
Bake covered at 450 degrees for 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours.

title: pasta aglio l'oglio
directions: Saute onion in a small pot until soft.
Add garlic and anchovies.
Cook slowly until garlic softens.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese; simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Pour over pasta.
Serve with cheese.

title: pimento and cheese sauce
directions: Cook the milk, dressing and sugar over low heat until sugar is melted and creamy.
Add the cubed cheese and stir constantly (will stick easy on low heat) until melted and creamy.
Add the pimentos and heat 1 more minute.
Very good while hot as dip for Townhouse crackers.
If too sweet, cut sugar.
Refrigerate overnight and make a delicious sandwich.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 15 minutes or till tender.
Mash potatoes, add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light.
Stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2 1/2 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.

title: fried chicken breasts
directions: Dip breasts in mixture of lemon pepper, salt, paprika, pepper, lemon juice and olive oil.
Heat olive oil and fry chicken breasts on both sides.
Enjoy.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar and cook until soft ball.
Add butter, peanut butter and add flavorings.
Mix thoroughly and pour out onto buttered platter.
Cut when cool.

title: icebox cake
directions: Put in mixing bowl in order given.
Mix well. Pack lightly in wafer box.
Tuck waxed paper in box around cake and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Stir in raisins (dredge with flour first).
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with unsweetened cocoa.
Combine the next 8 ingredients and beat on medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack. Let rest 1 minute before removing from pan.
Dust with sugar.

title: razor clam foo yong
directions: Heat frypan with 1/4-inch cooking oil.
Pour in batter to make 3 to 4-inch patties.
Cook until golden brown. Turn.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: cheese ball(with green peppers and pimientos)
directions: Mix well all but pecans. Form into ball. Roll in pecans.

title: veggie throw together
directions: Take some or all vegetables you like (depending on how much you want to make) and slice or chop into bite size pieces.
Boil all together until tender.
Drain and eat.
Mix plain or season with salt or butter.
Can spread over rice or noodles of your choice!
Enjoy.

title: spaghetti with clam and vegetable sauce
directions: Mince the garlic cloves.
Place the garlic and butter in a large, heavy pot over low heat until the butter is melted.
Add drained clams, saving juice.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add celery, zucchini, green onions, tomatoes and parsley.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add clam juice.
Taste for salt; you will probably not need it. If you do, add a trifle, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer the sauce until it has cooked down to a slightly thick consistency, at least 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti, with extra clam sauce on the side, to be added as wanted.
Top with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Before starting, preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until creamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until peaks.
Stir in chips, vanilla and nuts.
Place on a big cookie sheet, covered with foil or brown paper.
Turn oven off, put cookies in oven and leave for 4 or 5 hours.

title: cornish pastry crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening, blend and mix in cold water.
Roll out.
Place in shallow pan.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Combine egg, sour cream, milk and first 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add onion, salt, pepper, Monterey Jack, spinach and end with spaghetti.
Mix well.
Put in ungreased casserole.
Top with last 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, then the last 15 minutes, uncovered. Serves 3 to 4.
Easy to double or triple.
It is a wonderful side dish.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak up into small pieces.
Flour and brown both sides. Place meat into crock-pot.
Combine all ingredients into crock-pot.
Allow to cook all day.
Makes its own gravy.
May serve over rice or by self.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Take out 2/3 cup cake mix and set aside.
Mix the rest of the cake mix with 1/2 cup oleo and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix 2/3 cup cake mix and 1/2 cup brown sugar, salt, vanilla, Karo syrup and 3 eggs.
Pour over top of first layer and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook red beans until half done. Brown sausage and onion.
Add remaining ingredients to beans and simmer until done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Put strawberries in blender and puree.
Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries, add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and Cool Whip, in mixer and mix 2 minutes on medium.
Add nuts and bake in pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting with Cool Whip.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and celery salt.
Add sweet pepper, celery and onions.
Then add tomato juice, red pepper, paprika, chili powder, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours.
(May use garlic salt and oregano, if desired.)

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, flour and powdered sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pat dough into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potatoes a la renee
directions: Wash potatoes and wrap each potato in aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° until slightly soft.
Remove from oven and cool.
When potatoes are cooled, cut each potato into 1/2-inch to 1-inch round thick slices and place them in baking dish.
Then prepare topping.

title: 4th grade pasta primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and put in bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve with Italian bread.
Can be served warm or at room temperature.
Leftovers can be eaten cold.

title: my version of oriental pork chops
directions: Melt together first four ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to crumbs.
Dip meat and vegetables into the liquid and then into crumbs.
Arrange breaded chops in a Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with the breaded vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature for about 1 hour before starting.
Mix all cheeses and garlic salt together very thoroughly.
Add pecans into mixture.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring vanilla pudding, orange Jell-O and water to a boil, then let cool.
Add pineapple and juice, chopped pecans, then add Dream Whip prepared according to directions on package.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy pizza
directions: Toast bread on one side.
Place cheese on the untoasted side. Cover cheese with about 1 tablespoon of tomato sauce per slice. Sprinkle lightly with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice with green chilies
directions: Mix together sour cream and chilies; set aside.
Toss cheeses together.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Put half the rice in casserole; spread half the sour cream mixture on rice and top with half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover and bake an additional 10 minutes, or until bubbly.
May be assembled early in the day and baked later.
Can also be frozen before or after baking.
Serves 8.

title: crunchy wild rice pilaf
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions, except use apple juice or cider in place of 1 1/3 cups water and add a cup of water to equal 1/3 cup liquid.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to the water before cooking rice.
Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in 1 tablespoon butter, until crisp-tender.
About 5 minutes before rice is done, add water chestnuts, sauteed vegetables and parsley; stir with fork.
Cover and continue cooking until rice is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: deep-dish peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in 2/3 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with water while mixing lightly with a fork; form into a ball.
On lightly floured surface roll out 2/3 of dough to 13-inch square.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and slice zucchini.
Don't peel.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, carrot, sour cream and onion.
Add chicken, if desired.
Fold zucchini into mixture.
Add melted butter to stuffing.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs.
Spread the rest of the crumbs in large casserole, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Spoon vegetable mixture over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage pineapple tidbits
directions: Place muffin halves on greased baking sheet. Slowly fry sausage, breaking into small bits. Drain well. Add seasonings and pineapple. Spread muffins with tomato paste. Add a layer of sausage mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, then Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes. Cut into quarters.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Add bananas right before serving.

title: kandy kakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a jelly roll pan.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Spread one 8 ounce chocolate bar (melted) over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Add all other ingredients except for the sugar.
Boil down to make a thick sauce.
Add sugar and cook down.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together pineapple sugar, flour, and cheese in a greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Cover the top of mixture with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add onion.
Add all 3 cans of soup.
Top with frozen Tater Tots in a baking dish.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes; top with cheese.

title: barbecue table sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly; serve as a dipping sauce for brisket.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in greased muffin tins for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butterscotcherros
directions: Mix Karo syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat until it reaches a soft bubble.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Add Rice Krispies and blend well until all coated.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips together; spread over as frosting.

title: salad with a multitude of sins
directions: Stir gelatin and marshmallows in hot water until melted. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cheese, celery, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Add combined whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, oil and marshmallows over low heat or water. Pour over popcorn, peanuts and gumdrops.
Mix.
Pack in angel food pan, greased with butter.
Cool and cut.
Electric knife is nice.

title: egg omelet
directions: Place toast pieces in buttered dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Chill 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: 5 layer casserole
directions: First Layer:
Put shortening in skillet.
Brown beef and onions.
When partially brown add salt and chili powder and finish browning.
Peel and slice potatoes.

title: apple leather(homemade fruit roll-ups)
directions: Spread apple butter in buttered pan 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in 200°
oven overnight or at least 6 hours.
Cool, cut and keep in plastic Baggies.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Mix well and cook 40 minutes or until pie is done.
Shake.

title: easy tomato aspic
directions: Boil tomatoes 1 minute.
Add lemon jello and vinegar; mix well.
Pour into the tomato can until firm.
Unmold and slice. Delicious and easy!

title: speedy spaghetti casserole
directions: Fry ground beef, green pepper and onion.
In large bowl, chop canned spaghetti; add soup, cheese, soup mix, 1 teaspoon sugar and ground beef mixture.
Bake in casserole dish just long enough to heat through.

title: batter fried fish
directions: In medium bowl, mix together 1 cup flour, water, lemon juice, egg, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Dip fish in flour, then in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
This recipe is also great for frying shrimp, oysters and scallops.

title: hot onion cheese spread
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and brown.
Serve on crackers.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into five greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Cool on racks.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together well.
Great on grilled chicken and pork chops.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend together. Store in refrigerator. If you like the taste of dill, you may add some chopped dill pickles, or add dill pickle juice.
Serve with Ritz Crackers or your favorite cracker or chip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Milk is used to soften, if needed. Cut fresh pineapple into about 1/3 from top.
Stuff with dip.
Put fresh fruit on with toothpicks.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Take chicken off the bones and put in a casserole dish.
Crush tortilla chips and put over chicken. Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushroom soup and pour over chips.
Melt Velveeta and pour over mixture.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all and let stand for 24 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine
sugar,
water
and
syrup
in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, at a boil for 5 minutes.
Add peanuts and continue cooking
to 10 minutes, stirring until peanuts are turning golden brown.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour at once on
greased cookie sheet.
When cool, remove from pan and break into pieces.
Can substitute pecans instead of peanuts.

title: snow pea stir-fry
directions: Heat oil (or wine for no fat) in preheated wok and stir-fry snow peas 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry another minute. Combine stock, sugar, 5-spice powder and soy sauce.
Pour into mushroom-pea mixture and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: john's suzette sauce flambe!!!
directions: Melt butter in a chafing dish, then add sugar and allow to cook a few minutes.
Add orange juice and grenadine, stirring constantly.
Add the rolled pancakes, turning each in the sauce until well covered.
Add the liqueurs, light with a match, and turn pancakes, in flaming sauce, until the flame burns out.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Beat butter and sugar in mixer bowl at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
With mixer at low speed, beat in dry ingredients just until combined. Stir in coconut. Drop dough by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
With bottom of glass dipped in flour, flatten each cookie to 1/4-inch thickness, then press with back of fork to form ridges.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are golden.
Transfer to racks to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke heart salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni by directions on box; cool. Add olives, onions and artichoke hearts (with liquid). Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, juice and coloring together and let come to a boil.
Add Jell-O and let cool until it starts to congeal.
Whip condensed milk and add to other mixture.
Put into pie crust and put into refrigerator to firm up.
It can be frozen; wrap and freeze, removing one hour before serving.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix all together very well.
Cool and place in jars or plastic squeeze bottles.

title: broccoli salad with bacon
directions: Pour boiling water over broccoli to bring out green color; drain well.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces; put in a large bowl. Layer celery, green pepper and green peas over lettuce.
Mix salad dressing and sour cream.
Spread salad dressing mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle the cheese and bacon over the salad.
Cover the salad and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Toss the salad before serving.

title: raisin-nut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Turn mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Add jalapenos and salt to taste.
Serve over a block of cream cheese with chips or crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack together.
Preheat electric skillet at 225°.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Place meat loaf in electric skillet and bake, covered, with vent closed, for 30 minutes.
Carefully turn meat loaf to second side.
Continue to bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes, still covered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Butter 2 baking sheets and keep warm in oven.
Combine baking soda, vanilla and 1 teaspoon water in small bowl and set aside. Combine sugar, 1 cup water and syrup in large pot.
Cook over medium heat to 240° on the candy thermometer.
Stir in margarine and nuts.
Cook to 300° (stir constantly to keep from scorching). Immediately remove from heat and stir in baking soda mixture quickly.
Pour onto warm baking sheets and spread quickly.
Cool and break into pieces.
Stor tightly covered at room temperature. (Do not freeze.)

title: onion turnovers
directions: In a bowl, sift flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut in 3 tablespoons oil and gradually the water.
Mix thoroughly, adding a little flour, if necessary, until dough does not stick to bowl. Put aside.
Heat in a frying pan 1/4 cup oil and saute onion until golden.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll dough on a lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness and cut in 4-inch squares. Put in each square 1 tablespoon of sauteed onion, sprinkling with grated cheese.
Moisten the edges of the pastry and fold opposite corners together to form triangle, pressing the edges to seal.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Place bread, cheese and sausage/onion in 8-inch square casserole dish.
In bowl, whisk eggs and milk together until well blended.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, uncover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with toast.
Makes 4 to 5 servings. Recipe can be doubled.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add dry ingredients, 1/4 cup milk and bananas.
Mix until dampened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into tube or oblong pan.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and salt.
Then add cocoa to baking powder with hot water.
Then add flour and nuts.
Spread chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken on a biscuit
directions: Mix and heat peas, chicken, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place biscuits on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beef in bean barbecue bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce, onion and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 pound cheese.
Pour into a rectangle baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half, forming circle.
Place cut side down, around edge of casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: 24 hour punch
directions: Mix altogether and let it sit for 24 hours or more.
Strain and serve over ice.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until coarse.
Combine egg and orange juice and add to first mixture, only enough to mix lightly.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in bread pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Make corners higher than center.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 "valleys" in dry ingredients. Put in each valley the oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all and stir until no more flour shows.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet zucchini casserole
directions: Use 2 skillets.
In one skillet, saute onions and zucchini until tender.
In second skillet, brown meat; drain.
Combine two skillets and mix well.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and water chestnuts, if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer to combine flavors.
Sprinkle cheeses on top and cover to melt cheese.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight before serving with crackers.

title: johnnycake
directions: To make sour milk, place 1 tablespoon vinegar in bottom of cup and add milk.

title: brisket
directions: Cook in large pot with cover.
Rub meat with a mixture of onion powder, garlic powder, paprika and pepper.
Mix with cold water to form a paste.
Sear meat on both sides on a high heat. Add onion soup mix, beer, ketchup and cranberries.
Lower flame and cook, covered, 2 1/2 hours.
Slice when almost cooked to let meat absorb gravy.

title: new orleans seven bean soup
directions: Soak 2 cups of beans for 4 hours. Drain and rinse. Bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Add beans.
Cook on low for 2 hours. Cook sausage or hamburger and drain.
Add to beans.
Add onion, tomatoes, oregano and green pepper.
Add hot sauce and salt to taste. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: grilled peaches with raspberry puree
directions: Combine raspberries and lemon juice in container of an electric blender or food processor; top with cover, and process until smooth.
Strain raspberry puree, discard seeds.
Cover and chill.

title: brisket on grill
directions: Trim brisket and season with garlic salt, pepper, red pepper and Tony's seasoning; then rub whole brisket with Italian dressing. Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Mix together and put into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
(I bake my pie crust a little before adding filling.)

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and pat in pan the butter, flour and powdered sugar.
Bake at 325° for 14 minutes.
Mix together the eggs, lemon juice, sugar and flour.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until it starts turning brown.
Sift powdered sugar over top.

title: dill shrimp salad
directions: Shell, devein and steam shrimp for 3 to 5 minutes. Mix oil, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain shrimp mixture and add other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls and brown.

title: roast potato wedges
directions: Melt butter and oil in baking pan in 425° oven. Toss in potatoes;
add
seasonings.
Bake until tender and browned, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring mixture to full, rolling boil over high heat.
Add flour all at once. Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add cheese; stir to blend.

title: quick clam fritters
directions: Put
clams
and
onion	in
blender for 2 or 3 seconds. Pour into small mixing bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Gradually	add pre-mixed
flour and baking powder while beating with fork.
Mix just
enough
flour
to
make the fritters not too thick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg in bowl. Stir ketchup, water, soup mix, bread crumbs and ground beef. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: juanita's five hour stew
directions: In a large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Stir and cover with tight lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
(Do not open lid or check.)
Remove and stir before serving over rice, noodles or bread.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Split English muffin in half.
Butter and toast in broiler. Spread with tomato sauce, dash of oregano, American and Parmesan cheeses and toast under broiler until cheeses are melted.
Easy and great for kids!!

title: nutty peach pineapple cobbler
directions: Combine margarine and flour until mixture becomes crumblike. Stir in 2 tablespoons walnuts and mix in water 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough holds together.
Shape into ball.
Combine the rest of the walnuts, peaches, pineapple, cornstarch and allspice. Put into a 9-inch pie plate.
Roll dough to fit top of pie plate; place over filling.
Cut a 4-inch "X" in center of crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain and add seasoning package with about half the seasoning package of water.
Heat until most of water is absorbed. Put meat in shells and lay in pan.
Put salsa over top of burritos.
Sprinkle half package of each cheese over salsa.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start timer when mixture reaches full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well; spoon mixture onto wax papered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together.
Stir up well and put in unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: overnight salad
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler.
Add vinegar, sugar and butter.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool.

title: lo-cal beef stew for two
directions: To Vary Stew:
Add
mushrooms,	beef broth, egg noodles (omit potatoes), bell pepper, hot pepper, etc.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and add butter, milk and lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes or until set.

title: muffin pizzas
directions: Season tomato sauce to taste with salt, pepper, and oregano, or any other favorite spices.
Spread 2 Tbsp. of mixture on each muffin half.
Add slice of mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with parmesan cheese and anything else you like.
Preheat oven to 350. Bake for 15-20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients, pour into the prepared dish.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, bring to room temperature and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the fruit cocktail and vanilla and add dry ingredients.
Beat well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Keep warm. Blend flour into drippings; stir until smooth.
Stir in bean liquid juice, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Add green beans and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle bacon on top just before serving.

title: thelma's party mix
directions: Melt margarine in pan in oven; sprinkle garlic powder over margarine.
Pour Worcestershire sauce on, then pour in other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: soupy pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in an oblong casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave at 70 percent for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Stir-fry cabbage, celery and onion in butter in a heavy Dutch oven for 5 minutes over high heat.
Cover and remove from heat. Let steam until cabbage is tender (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: slow cooked beef
directions: Mix soups and the one half can of water together and pour over meat mixture in roasting pan.
Cook in a slow oven, 250°, for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: * homemade vanilla ice cream *
directions: Combine sugar, beaten eggs, half and half, whipping cream and vanilla.
Place in freezer and add enough milk to fill freezer 3/4 full.
Mix well.
Makes 1 gallon.
Other ingredients can be added (peaches, fresh strawberries, etc.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Makes 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish. Sprinkle with onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Turn and sprinkle other side.
Slice margarine over chicken pieces. Sprinkle paprika over chicken. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until juice runs clear.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and brown almonds.
Add sugar, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Mix. Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over it.
Top with remaining mixture.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer just before eating so it will be ready by dessert time.

title: serita's sausage on rye
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix the sausage, cheese, oregano and basil together in an electric skillet. Spread the sausage mixture on the rye bread and bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Blend all ingredients 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian farmer sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with softened butter.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Divide equally on unbuttered side of 6 slices of bread; top with 6 slices (1 each) Mozzarella cheese.
Top with other slices of bread, butter side out.
Grill on both sides until cheese starts to melt and bread is golden.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Beat the egg; stir in a little more than 1/2 c. milk.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash and pierce potatoes with fork.
Arrange potatoes in microwave. Cook on Full power for 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes. Bake several more minutes until potatoes are done.
When done, slice off the top of the potato and scoop out the inside.
In mixing bowl, add all ingredients except paprika; beat until smooth.
Spoon back into potato shells.
Garnish with paprika. Heat in microwave for 3 minutes or put in oven to brown.
Potatoes can be topped with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: hearts-a-fire chili(kids in the kitchen)
directions: Brown beef in skillet over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain excess fat. Add chopped onion. Cook 5 minutes more. Stir in chili mix, tomatoes, water and beans.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for at least 30 minutes. Serve in soup bowls over rice, if desired.
Shredded cheese and chopped pepper can be sprinkled on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over direct heat.
Add onion.
Cook slowly until soft but not golden.
Blend in flour. Add milk gradually.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place pan over boiling water for 20 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date straws
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs light and mix all together.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in large pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a moderate oven.
Leave until cold.
Cut in strips. Roll each strip in powdered sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put in dish and set aside.

title: nine day coleslaw
directions: Shred the cabbage, onions and peppers.
Bring following to a rolling boil and pour over shredded mixture:
sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Chill; serve.
Good stuff, even better after several days.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spoon sour cream over top. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Tear tortillas into 50 cent size pieces. Combine soups, chicken broth, chopped onion, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, cook milk and sugar to the soft ball stage. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish or pie pan.

title: broccoli with shells and sausage
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage in 1/4 cup olive oil. Add rest of oil and
garlic
and
saute
to
light
brown; put aside. Cook broccoli
until
tender.
Cook
shells
as usual. Drain broccoli and shells.
Put
in
large bowl.	Drizzle with sausage and oil and
toss
gently.	Add
crushed hot pepper to taste and grated Italian cheese.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in drained pineapple, then coconut and nuts. Pour into pie shells. Chill for 3 hours.

title: yummy bars
directions: Pack into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour and sugars.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Coat pecans with mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with seasoned salt.

title: our barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter on stove top or in microwave in a medium bowl. Stir in catsup, mustard, Worcestershire, brown sugar, lemon juice and season to taste.
Baste over any meat.

title: banana holiday bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, baking powder and salt until fluffy. Mix in half of the flour. Add bananas and milk, blend well. Stir in remaining flour, candied fruit, raisins and nuts. Turn into a greased 9x5x3 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 60-70 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool before slicing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the Knox gelatine and 1/4 cup water; set aside. Stir 3/4 cup sugar and half and half and cook to boiling; remove from heat. Add vanilla, sour cream and Knox gelatine mixture; mix well. Pour into 9 x 9 dish. Let set up in refrigerator about 2 to 4 hours.

title: helen's chocolate logs
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, pecans and cracker crumbs into peanut butter.
Pour melted butter over the mixture and blend well. Shape dough into 2 x 1/2-inch logs.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together over boiling water.
Work quickly; dip logs into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper to dry (use a fork for the dipping).
Be sure to leave chocolate mixture over hot water while dipping.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer in large bowl in listed order. Drop on greased cookie sheets, 1 tablespoon each cookie, 2 inches apart.
Makes 40 cakes (2 1/2-inches each) or 20 pies.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
When cool, make Filling.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Put small amount of milk, chilies, cream cheese, butter and garlic salt together.
Melt in microwave; stir and add corn. Serve hot.

title: josie's coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend until well mixed. Place batter in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° and continue to bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all of ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Make a slight depression in meat loaf and pour in your favorite catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave on High for 12 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven
Mix all dry ingredients, except raisins and dates.
In saucepan, bring honey, oil, vanilla and corn syrup
to
a
boil.
Mix hot liquid into dry ingredients. Bake 30
minutes,
stirring
every 5 minutes.
Add raisins and dates.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: one hour cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine
tablespoons butter and warm buttermilk in a bowl. Mix
yeast	and
2	tablespoons
sugar in a small bowl. Stir in
a small amount of warm milk mixture.
Pour back into milk mixture and mix well.
Knead on a floured surface and add enough
flour to make workable dough.
Roll very thin.
Spread with mixture	of butter, cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar.
Roll and slice;
makes 36. Place in greased pan.
Let rise 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot. Drizzle with glaze.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: brown bag divinity
directions: Beat egg whites very
stiff.
Gradually
add
sugar and cream of tartar.	Beat
very
well.
Slowly
add	vinegar
and vanilla, while still beating.
Cut
brown
bag
little
larger than cookie sheet (use inside
of
bag).
Drop	by teaspoon on sheet 1 inch apart.
Place pecan
half
on each.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes. Let cool on
cookie sheet of brown paper bag. For
Christmas candy, add few drops of red or green cake color before baking.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Slice 2 bananas.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Fold chocolate and bananas into sugar mixture.
Pour into cool pie shells.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Before serving, add bananas to top.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: rich peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in peanut butter and shortening.
Stir in milk and eggs, beaten together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes one loaf.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix and pour Sweet and Sour Sauce over sauce mix:

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage. Spread over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash and onion casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; drain.
Salt to taste. Put in small casserole or baking dish.
Pour soup over squash. Add grated cheese and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: new england style baked beans
directions: Cut into wedges.
Steam for 15 minutes.
Put on sheet pan, cover with melted butter.
Add parsley, white pepper, garlic salt or garlic powder, paprika and Schilling cheese bread sprinklers, to taste.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: stuffed spinach shells
directions: Put all ingredients together and stuff precooked shells.
Heat with spaghetti sauce until hot.

title: noel cookie gems
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease sheets.
In a large bowl, combine shortening, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients. Add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Mix well.
Shape into 1 to 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in nuts, if used.
Place 1-inch apart on greased sheet.
Press thumb in center of each cookie.
Fill with jam, jelly, preserves or cherry.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: easy vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: elegant lemon cake roll
directions: Grease bottom
and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan with vegetable oil.
Line with wax paper and grease and flour wax paper.
Set aside.

title: honey-sesame cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Beat butter, honey and egg until fluffy; stir in sesame seeds.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Chill dough three hours; remove from refrigerator and roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Gently flatten each ball. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: gratin of potatoes and parsnips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large (9 x 12-inch) baking dish with 1 tablespoon butter.
Arrange one-third of the potatoes in the bottom followed by half the parsnips.
Scatter half the onions over the top.
Drizzle with a third of the butter and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a generous grinding of pepper. Repeat.
Finish with last layer of potatoes, evenly arranged, the remaining butter and top with a last 1/2 teaspoon salt, some pepper and the cheese.
Pour on the cream.
It should come just to the surface of the potatoes.
If not, add up to 2 cups chicken stock.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and bake 15 minutes longer or until brown and bubbling.

title: mom's cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Prepare chicken in bite size pieces.
Can be done day before. Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa.

title: bubble bread
directions: Bring pudding mix, sugar, oleo and milk to a slow boil.
Remove from heat.
Pull 1 loaf of bread dough apart in small balls and layer on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of syrup over balls and sprinkle with half of the cinnamon.
Repeat with the second loaf, syrup and cinnamon.
Cover and let raise to the top edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto foil or serving plate.

title: water chestnuts in bacon
directions: Drain liquid from one can of water chestnuts.
Add those chestnuts to the other can and its liquid.
Add soy sauce and garlic salt.
Stir and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, drain liquid (chestnuts will be brown).
Wrap each chestnut with bacon strip; secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Can be done ahead and reheated.

title: pot roast
directions: Wash meat and trim off any fat.
Sear (brown) on all sides in butter using high temperature.
Add tomato soup, water, onion, bay leaves and fines herbes.
Cook meat and sauce on low or simmer for 4 1/2 hours (2 to 3 pounds meat), 30 minutes longer for each additional pound of meat.
When done, remove meat from sauce and cut.
To sauce add 3 teaspoons of cornstarch that have been premixed with 1/4 to 1/2 cup water (mixture just thin enough to pour).
Stir for a few minutes until it thickens.
Place meat back in sauce.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: nehi ambrosia
directions: Chill in freezer for 45 minutes and serve.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Put white sugar, cream of tartar and water in a saucepan; bring to full boil.
Drop in Ritz crackers.
Let boil for 2 minutes, with no stirring.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Top with brown sugar and cinnamon; put dots of butter on top.
Add top crust.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, or until crust is done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Boil together vinegar, brown sugar, mustard and cloves.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat egg in small bowl; add milk, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla. Combine with flour mixture and mix until just moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tin filling 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes. May add chocolate chips to batter.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onions and butter.
Add other ingredients.
When cool, add beaten eggs.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 of stuffing mix.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and top with reserved mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash and apple casserole
directions: Cut each squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in a lightly greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with apple slices.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well. Spoon over apple slices.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until squash is tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix fruits and nuts with 1 cup of the flour.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, fruit and nuts.
Add flour, soda and sweet milk with cinnamon.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven.
Do not overcook.
Can freeze before or after baking.
Makes approximately 100 cookies. These mellow with age.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles
until
tender,
add other ingredients and pour into baking
dish.
Top
with buttered crumbs and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: clam dip pie
directions: Mix can of clam sauce with Ritz cracker bits.
Arrange in pie plate.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Serve with crackers.

title: sauerkraut and ribs
directions: In a large Pyrex dish or Dutch oven, place sauerkraut and then ribs on top of kraut and bake covered with lid or foil for about 2 hours at 350°. Remove foil and cook about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stoney's strawberry ice
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and gelatin; stir in 1 cup of water.
Heat and stir over medium heat until sugar and gelatin dissolve.
Remove from heat; add remaining water, berries and lemon juice.
Freeze in container until firm.
Break into chunks. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Return to container; freeze firm.
Let stand at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey meatball skillet dinner
directions: In medium bowl, combine turkey, bread crumbs, egg, pepper, green onion and parsley; mix well.
Shape into 15 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Heat margarine and garlic in large, nonstick skillet over medium heat about 1 minute.
Add turkey meatballs.
Cook and stir until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Turn heat to low and add vegetables.
Cook and stir 6 to 8 minutes or until meatballs are no longer pink in color.

title: milo's raisin supreme
directions: Bring all
ingredients	to
a
boil, then cook on low 2 hours. Serve over ice cream, cakes or puddings.

title: cabbage beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet,
add onions,
peppers, and rice.
Cook until peppers and onions are tender.
Cut cabbage in small strips and put in dish.
Pour ground beef mixture over top of cabbage.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Add more juice if needed.

title: kevin's mom's homemade spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: watermelon milkshake
directions: Separate seeds from slices of watermelon.
Place watermelon pieces in blender; churn until it turns to a liquid.
Add approximately an equal amount of vanilla ice cream or enough to make any desired thickness.
Usually no sugar or milk is needed. Pour into tall glasses; provide a straw and spoon.

title: instant cocoa mix(1 gallon dry mix)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Store in an airtight one gallon container.
To serve, fill a mug half-full of the mixture; finish filling with water and stir until blended. Heat in microwave oven on Full power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until warmed.

title: mints
directions: Mix together and pour in small candy molds or drop on waxed paper.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter and shape into balls. Melt chocolate with wax and balls to coat.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring sugar and water to boiling.
Add tea bags and 7 spices tied loosely in cheesecloth bag.
Steep 5 minutes.
Add juice of orange and lemon.

title: creamy chicken lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Coat 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Combine chicken soup and 2/3 cup milk in large bowl. Spoon 1/4 cup of milk mixture over bottom of prepared baking dish. Add chicken and corn to remaining soup and milk mixture in bowl. Stir together the Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses in another large bowl.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: Mince garlic.
Grate or shred red cabbage.
Saute garlic and cabbage in oil.
Add apples, cut into chunks.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.
Good with pork roast.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 inch cake pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle over top of batter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 60 minutes.
Let cool and pour glaze over top of cake.

title: spiced walnuts(this recipe is from the 16th century.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Heat over medium temperature until liquid boils.
Stir constantly until liquids evaporate and nuts are coated with sugar.
Spread on a nonstick cookie sheet and allow to cool.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Melt butter.
Mix butter and sugar together.
Add to eggs.
Mix lemon juice and vanilla into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let pie cool.

title: chocolate sauce(this is not low-fat, but it's good!)
directions: Shake together in 20 ounce canister the sugar, cocoa powder, cornstarch and salt.
Add and stir in water on low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Store in the fridge.

title: cheese & broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together milk, pudding and Cool Whip; set aside.
Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Combine the 2 mixtures and then layer with crushed Oreos.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half with decorator knife.
Remove egg yolks, rinse out egg whites.
Put upside down on towel to drain dry. Press egg yolks and mix with other ingredients.
Fill egg whites and decorate with sliced olive.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until brown. Add celery, onion and pepper. Saut until tender. Stir in chicken, broth, rice and Cajun seasoning. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat to simmer. Simmer for 45 minutes. Liquid should be absorbed. Remove from heat. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: unbelievable lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender container, combine all ingredients except coconut.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti to directions.
Add butter and cheese while hot.
Add eggs and quickly mix again.
Make crust in 10-inch deep pie pan.
Cover with 1 cup cottage cheese.
Cover with favorite spaghetti sauce.
Cook down until very thick or add 1 package Lawry's spaghetti sauce mix to thicken.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake date balls
directions: Combine dates, salt, sugar, egg and butter in saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in cereal, walnuts and vanilla.
Roll into balls (butter hands first).
Roll in powdered sugar, if desired.

title: ham, cheese and broccoli quiche
directions: Melt butter.
Add ham and onion.
Lightly brown.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Heat oven to 375°.
Press liquid from broccoli by blotting between paper towels.
Toss broccoli in flour.
In medium bowl, lightly beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Stir in cooled ham and onion mixture. Add broccoli and 1 cup cheese.
Pour onto unbaked pie shell. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle more cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes.

title: calabasitas
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil; add zucchini and saute for about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, chilies and tomato sauce.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and add cilantro and cheese.
Simmer for about 15 minutes until cheese is melted and zucchini is tender.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press hamburger in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with canned milk, salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes over milk.
Slice onions over potatoes. Cube cheese on top of onions.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Uncover and brown top.
Makes 6 servings.
Add a green salad and you have a quick meal.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil or use nonstick cooking spray to coat a 10-inch cast-iron frying pan.
Scatter celery slices in pan.
Add chicken breasts, meaty side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: gladys jones' raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, bring raisins and 1 3/4 cups water to boil for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining water with brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into raisin mixture and return to boiling.
Remove from heat and add vinegar, salt and butter.
Pour into unbaked 9 to 10-inch pie crust.
Add top crust and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, sour cream and soda.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in pan.
Put mix on wax paper and mash it down; cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in pan with melted butter.
Pour other half over biscuits before cooking at 425°.

title: dr. suess' green eggs and ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Slice top crust off and carefully hollow out loaf, leaving 3/4-inch thick.
Brush all with butter.
Place on cookie sheet in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Keep warm.
Beat eggs frothy.
Combine in blender the milk, parsley, chives, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Put green mixture into eggs and mix well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Get hot and scramble eggs.
Add ham.
Spoon eggs into "croustade."
Sprinkle with chives and parsley.
Fun and good.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: diabetic cinnamon cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Blend in shortening.
Mix Sweet*10, milk and vanilla together.
Stir into flour mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough.
Mix a bit.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Stir and pour into freezer.

title: chicken kellaguin
directions: Using a fork, separate chicken from bones.
Remove skin, if you desire, and then shred chicken.
Add chicken, coconut, green onions and red pepper flakes.
Mix thoroughly.
When dish is ready to be served, add lemon juice; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serves 4.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour, beat in lemon extract and 7-Up, pour batter into well-greased and floured jumbo fluted mold.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Cook remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions, without salt.
Meanwhile, place milk, apples, water, cottage cheese, sugar and egg whites in blender container.
Blend until smooth.

title: creamy spinach and carrot soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until onions are tender.
Stir in flour until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking over low heat, stirring occasionally until soup is heated thoroughly, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crescent rolls bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 can of crescent rolls.
Beat cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Put over crescent rolls.
Top with second can of rolls.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup of chopped nuts. Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious dessert.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Grease pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Spread croutons on bottom and sprinkle cheese over
croutons.
Brown
and
drain sausage and put over cheese.
Beat	rest
of
ingredients, except soup and 1/2 can milk, and
pour
over.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Before putting in oven mix mushroom
soup
and
1/2 can milk and pour over top. Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and blend into egg mixture.	Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface, cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheet immediately, sprinkle with sugar if desired.

title: corn and pepper bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch round baking pan. Combine flour, meal, sugar, powder, soda and salt in large bowl. Mix buttermilk, margarine and egg.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture until combined.
Fold in pepper and chilies. Put batter into greased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice for beverage.
Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Place a half walnut on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and
discard the grease.
Add remaining ingredients except beans and
salt.
Simmer
for
to
3 hours. In the last 30 minutes, add beans and salt.
Serves 12 to 15. This recipe is easy to half and freezes well.

title: butter riches
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Shape into long rolls.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice.
Top with nut.
Bake until very lightly brown, 7 to 9 minutes, at 350°. Party cookies.

title: delicious baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: smash
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Remove from heat. Add orange juice and lemonade. Stir. Add gin or vodka.
Stir.
Freeze in plastic container for at least 36 hours. When serving, scoop out mixture to fill glass. Slowly add 7-Up or Sprite until glass fills.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add chicken broth and broccoli; semi-boil until broccoli is tender.
Lower heat and add cheese cubes. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add garlic powder and milk. Mix cornstarch with water until dissolved.	Add to soup and cook until desired thickness.
I have used a bag of frozen mixed cauliflower and broccoli when making this soup.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, cocoa and Pet milk.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring at 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter (to taste) and marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted. Pour in buttered dish.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Sift the sugar, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt into a bowl.
In a larger bowl, mix the eggs, crushed pineapple, oil, vanilla, coconut, carrots and pecans.
Add the dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Bake in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool for 1 hour.

title: vegetables oriental
directions: In 10-inch skillet combine broth, cornstarch, ginger, sugar, sherry and soy sauce.
Over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with almonds before serving.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease angel food cake pan well.
Melt margarine on very low heat in saucepan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit quarters, a few at a time, to coat well.
Place pieces in pan, adding chopped nuts after each layer.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon with melted margarine.
Pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: basic ham and bean soup
directions: Bring broth, or water, to a boil and add beans, ham bone, carrots, celery, onion, garlic, mustard and bay leaves. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and let simmer for 60 minutes. Remove ham bone and discard. Stir in chopped ham and simmer 30 more minutes. Season with ground white pepper to taste.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan; pour chopped nuts evenly over bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: kosy's chicken bites
directions: Debone chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces. Marinate overnight in 1 1/2 cups buttermilk and Ranch dressing. Dip in flour, turmeric, salt and pepper and fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cut peeled potatoes into chunks and boil until very soft. Drain.
Add margarine and, using mixer, beat until margarine is melted and well blended.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except marshmallows and mix by hand.
Put in ovenproof casserole dish; top with marshmallows and toast in oven.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Gradually blend soup into cream cheese, using an electric mixer.
Beat just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 2 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Note:
One cup chopped pecans and/or chocolate chips may be added (optional).

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes for 25 minutes, then peel and cube potatoes. Add all other ingredients together, except eggs.
Add in potatoes and eggs with other mixture.
Chill for 6 to 24 hours, covered.

title: bat-a-pie
directions: Melt margarine into pan.
Pour batter into it, then pour canned fruit into batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco-flavored corn chips salad
directions: Set aside 1 tablespoon of taco seasoning for the dressing (recipe follows).
Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Let cool.
Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce and then browned meat, cheese, beans, onion and tomatoes.
Add dressing and crushed chips.
Can mix all layers together or keep it layered.
Serve.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Roll out biscuits, one at a time.
Put small layer of sausage over flattened biscuit.
Roll biscuit and sausage into a log and slice in small sections.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Make into patties and fry in shallow fat.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over meatballs. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add baking soda to applesauce (will become foamy), then add applesauce to sugar and butter mix. Sift flour and spices and add to mixture. Stir in raisins.
Pour in buttered loaf pan and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine with electric mixer.
Add egg, cream or milk and vanilla.
Chill dough.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: molasses drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses and egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate bits and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: leftover casserole
directions: Mix in casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove and add sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla mocha drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix together.
Add 3 rounded tablespoonfuls to hot water.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Bring above ingredients, except rice, to boil in large pan. Add 1 cup raw rice.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in casserole or roaster and bake at 350° until rice is soft, approximately 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fried mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls in deep hot grease until brown.

title: baked fish
directions: Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Melt enough butter and prepared mustard to cover fish.
Dip fish in cornmeal, then brush both sides with butter and mustard mixture.
Place on foil and bake for about 25 minutes.
Then turn fish over and bake another 25 minutes or until fish is brown.
Bake at 400°.
You can use fillets or pieces.

title: oatmeal and date cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients along with dates.
Mix well.
Then add orange juice and mix thoroughly.
Place onto sprayed Pam cookie sheet by using a tablespoon of batter dropped in place. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: no egg wonder cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until almost smooth. Pour into greased pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with your favorite icing.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together and add other ingredients. Pour into pan, let set.
Cut and serve.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Reserve juice from water chestnuts.
In skillet, saute next 4 ingredients in bacon drippings.
Using reserved juice from chestnuts, dilute soup.
Add next 2 ingredients to sauteed vegetables.
Pour into greased casserole and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Dot top of casserole with butter.

title: my man's cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients. Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: easy guacamole
directions: Mash avocados together. Add desired fresh squeezed lime or lemon juice and salt on avocados. Mix all ingredients well. If you desire a hot taste leave in seeds of jalapeno pepper.
Take out seeds if you desire a milder taste.

title: corn tortillas tostada
directions: Cut corn tortillas into squares in diamonds as small or as big that you want.
To make cut
outs,
use pinking shears. Warm Wesson oil, not very hot.
Place
tortillas
cut-outs
in frying pan basket.
Place in oil and fry slowly to a crackling sound. Get out; add salt.
Serve cold or
hot
with
dips
or chili sauce.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender. Drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayo, peas and salt.
Blend soup and milk.
Heat through.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts. Add to noodle mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: oven roasted potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 450°, leaving skin on.
Scrub potatoes thoroughly and cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips.

title: ignesis fudge
directions: Cook slowly until chocolate melts, stirring.
Boil without stirring until the mixture forms a firm ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons of butter and beat until thick.
Pour into pan and place in refrigerator to cool quickly--extrusive!
Intrusive; cool slowly.
Do not beat and let it cool on the countertop.

title: rice krispies cereal bars
directions: In heavy pan, bring sugar, syrup and butter to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix well together.
Spread quickly on buttered jelly roll pan.
Pat lightly.
Melt chips together. Spread over cereal for frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: picante surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving. Great dip for chips, crackers, raw vegetables and can be used on baked chicken for a real treat. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: chocolate topped cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Using the back of the spoon, firmly press mixture on bottom and side of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate. Refrigerate while preparing filling.

title: corn puffs
directions: Mix together eggs, flour, baking powder and spices.
Add corn kernels.
Fry spoonfuls in hot oil.
Makes 4 dozen puffs.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla with mixer.
Add flour last. Drop on baking sheet.
Bake until light brown at 350°.
One teaspoon of batter makes one cookie.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Store in refrigerator.

title: punch for all occasions
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups water; add rest of ingredients. Just before serving, pour over crushed ice and add the ginger ale last. Serves 20 people. Easy to double or triple.

title: chocolate bourbon balls
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, almonds and 2 cups powdered sugar in large bowl.
Stir in bourbon and corn syrup.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least five days to blend flavors.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: uncooked fruitcake
directions: Mix in a large pan over low heat.
Pack in loaf pans.
Let set several days or weeks.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix nuts, flour and butter by hand.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and pat dough in pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
With electric mixer, beat cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Blend in 1 large tub of Cool Whip and spread mixture on top of crust.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: hummus
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor and blend together.
Add reserved liquid a little at a time to bring the hummus to a peanut butter state.
Serve with warm pita bread.

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans in colander with cold water; drain all beans.
Add the green pepper and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over beans.
Let marinate overnight.
Keeps for days in refrigerate.

title: congo cookies
directions: Mix margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and pinch of salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Spread on well greased flat tin.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff.
Add 1 cup brown sugar gradually and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread on batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: corn relish
directions: Remove seeds from 1 pepper only, chop cabbage, celery and onions.
Add all other ingredients except corn.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add corn and cook 15 minutes longer.
Can and seal while hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Melt margarine and saute onion. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Combine soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, Velveeta and sauteed onion.
Add chicken and then spaghetti.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
