In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
If mix is too moist, add a little more flour.
Drop by level tablespoon onto Pam sprayed cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: jamaican baby back ribs
directions: For seasoning rub, combine all ingredients except ribs in a small bowl and mix well.
Spread over all surfaces of ribs; press with fingertips so mixture adheres to ribs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: bulldog brittle
directions: Break graham crackers into fourths.
Place in foil lined 10 x 15-inch baking pan, leaving space between crackers.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Melt margarine and butter in top of double boiler.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes exactly.
Pour over graham crackers and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: creamy egg nog punch
directions: Scoop ice cream into punch bowl.
Mix egg nog with ice cream, sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon and stir in cool whip.
Serve immediately.

title: yummy bar cookies
directions: Mix butter with brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Spray 11 x 16 inch jelly roll pan with vegetable spray. Line pan with Crispy saltines, placed touching.
Pour brown sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle chocolate morsels over top and let melt.
Top with chopped pecans.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut; roll in balls.
Roll in coconut.
Put in the refrigerator.

title: helman's cookies
directions: Blended Oatmeal:
Measure and blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Jiffy mix.
Then add the muffin mix and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes and bread(or "please mam")
directions: In large pot, cook tomatoes for about 20 minutes, then add ingredients.
Break bread up into small pieces.
Put the mixture into a buttered dish or pan and put into oven at 400° until brown on top.

title: chicken divine
directions: Brown cut-up chicken breasts.
Mix in celery soup and chicken soup.
Add celery salt, salt and pepper.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pudding cookie surprise
directions: Combine pudding and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Place plastic wrap on surface of pudding.
Chill.
Combine crumbs, nuts and butter, mixing well.
Place about 2 tablespoons crumb mixture in each of 6 dessert glasses.
Stir pudding and spoon into glasses; sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned spicy apple butter(not so sweet)
directions: Prepare apples as stated.
Cook.
Run through sieve as for applesauce.
Heat in large kettle, adding remaining ingredients. Cook for 45 minutes.
Place in sterile jars and add heated lids. Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in the microwave until soft.
Stir in noodles and walnuts; mix well.
Spoon drop mixture on a platter, let stand for 10 minutes and serve.
What could be easier!

title: squash patties
directions: Beat together and spoon out in patties.
Fry in oil.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Dust with 10x sugar if desired.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Place cabbage in boiling, salted water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix 1/3 cup
cheese with cream sauce; add cabbage.
Put in well-greased casserole.
Add other 1/3 cup cheese and croutons, buttered, on top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, covered, until last few minutes.

title: hopi indian blue cornmeal cakes
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, oil and salt.
Add milk to give consistency you prefer for griddlecakes.
For thicker cakes, use 1 cup.
For thinner cakes, use 1 1/2 cups.
Stir just until lumps disappear; do not overmix.

title: breaded veal-wiener schnitzel
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Dip steak in egg and milk mixture; dip in cracker crumbs.
Repeat procedure.
In lightly oiled frying pan, brown on both sides.
Place in oblong pan with 1/4 cup water. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Put egg in standard measuring cup and beat lightly.
Fill to 1 cup level with milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to this milk and egg mixture and beat a little to blend well.
Let stand to rise, about 5 minutes.
Drop batter by tablespoon on top of boiling stew.
Cover and boil 20 minutes or until done.

title: apple smoothie
directions: In blender, whirl applesauce until very smooth.
Add orange juice.
Whirl again.
Pour into tall glass; add ice.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix white cake mix and jello.
Add oil, milk and eggs beating all the time.
Add strawberries, coconut and pecans, then mix them in.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix apples, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
In 8 x 8-inch greased and floured baking pan, spoon apples corner to corner.
Mix all other ingredients and spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fast fixin fruit n cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pour oil into a 9 x 13 pan; tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put cake mix, eggs, and water into pan; stir with a fork until blended (about 2 min.)
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Spoon pie filling onto batter; use a fork to fold into batter just enough to create a marbled effect. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 50 minutes; until toothpick comes out clean.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Use a knife to loosen cake from sides; cut and serve directly from pan. Makes 16 to 20 servings.
Store cake loosely covered.

title: egg casserole
directions: Drain grease from bacon and sausage. Beat eggs and milk together. Layer bread, sausage, bacon and half of egg mixture in a 9 x 13 pan. Repeat second layer. Place grated cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate miracle whip cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a sealed container. Refrigerate for 2 days.

title: sausage appetizer
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck until crumbly.
Melt cheese (in chunks) in microwave.
Combine meats and cheese.
Spread on rye cocktail bread and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice.
Add fruit and chill.
Chill fruits before mixing.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut and pecans and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour mixture over the pecan-coconut mixture.
Do not stir!
Set aside.
In the microwave, melt together cream cheese and margarine.
Put on 30 seconds high.
Stir.
Put on 30 seconds on high.
Stir, etc., until creamy, then add powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Do not stir!
Bake cake for 50 to 60 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool and flip onto cake plate.

title: dago dish
directions: Layer ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Layer again and top with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 1/2 hour to melt cheese.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add yolks, alternate dry ingredients with water.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Grease 2 (10-inch) pans and flour. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until when touched it will spring back.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Batter will be thick.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan (or tube pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: curried split pea soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan over medium heat, cook onion, garlic and bacon until bacon is translucent.
Add split peas and water. Bring mixture to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer until peas are tender (about 1 hour).
Meanwhile, split carrot lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Thinly slice carrot and celery; set aside.

title: broccoli-cheddar soup
directions: Bring 3 quarts of water to a boil in a Dutch oven; add broccoli and cook 7 minutes until tender.
Drain; set aside.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble bread and bacon into bite-size pieces and set aside. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and pickle juice.
Pour this over tomatoes, peppers, onion and pickles.
Then add to bread mixture and toss well.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: yummy caramel squares
directions: Blend shortening with sugar and egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture with milk and vanilla.

title: oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, spices and baking powder. Add dry ingredients to sugar mix.
Add oats and pecans; mix well. Roll into balls.
Put on pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, soda and salt to mixture and mix well.
Add oatmeal. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix all the above together in a mixing bowl.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Freeze for at least 12 hours.
Set out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and melted butter.
Bake in an uncooked pie shell at 350° until done.
Top with meringue.

title: easy scalloped tomatoes
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of buttered baking dish with
crumbs. Add tomatoes mixed with onions and seasonings.
Top with
remaining
crumbs;
dot with butter. Bake 15 minutes or until browned.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lady norma relish
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Chop fine or put through meat grinder.
Add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain in a.m.
Add onions, vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed and celery seed.
Cook over medium heat for one hour.
Add red pepper for color if desired.
Seal in jars.

title: tomato corn chowder
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery and carrot in 3 tablespoons butter until tender (approximately 10 minutes). Dump in big pot and add potatoes, tomatoes, corn and pulp, salt, pepper, basil and chicken stock. Simmer
35 minutes. Add the cup of cream just before serving and reheat (don't boil).

title: pueblo pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and spices.
Stir in raisins.
Mix together other ingredients and add flour mixture. Blend well.
Pour batter into two oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine chili powder and onion salt.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Add corn, olives and 1/4 cup of the crushed tortilla chips.
Mix well.
Turn mixture onto an 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup crushed tortilla chips and Cheddar cheese.
Bake about 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fried chicken
directions: Put oil in a large skillet, preferably cast-iron.
Heat on medium to high heat.
Salt chicken slightly.
In a medium size brown paper bag, put flour, a little salt and paprika.
Shake well. Put in 4 or 5 pieces of chicken and shake to coat well.
Test oil by dropping in a pinch of flour.
If it sizzles, put in the chicken.
Fry until light brown on bottom side.
Turn and continue frying until color is uniform, about 15 minutes per side.
Remove to paper towels and drain oil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: beer and bacon spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and drain on absorbent paper.
To bacon fat in skillet, add onions and garlic; saute until golden.
Add ground meat and cheese; stir often and cook until browned.
Add beer and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, parsley flakes, oregano and basil; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Add tomato puree, mushrooms and bacon; continue cooking until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Add some sauce to cooked spaghetti and toss lightly.
Serve remaining sauce in separate bowl.
Any leftover sauce may be frozen if desired.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: granola
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; in another bowl, mix the next 4 ingredients with a whip or hand beater thoroughly.
The honey in the mixture helps mix the oil and water together.
Pour the oil mixture into the oats mixture. Mix with hands until all ingredients are well coated.
Spread the mix on oiled cookie sheets and bake in oven at 200° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn mixture thoroughly after the first 1/2 hour and again every 15 minutes until oats are light golden brown.
Remove from oven and stir again.
Let cool.
Add raisins or other dried fruits.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: andrea's corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 20 minutes.
Mix melted Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add to raisin and water mixture.
Sift remaining dry ingredients.
Add raisin sauce.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Stir soup into mayonnaise. Toss with turkey mixture.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: taco pie
directions: Thaw crust.
Heat oven to 400°. Prick pie crust, sides and bottom.
Bake in oven 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°.

title: "bahama smile"(straight from the bahamas)
directions: Blend the ingredients and serve over crushed ice.

title: potato dish
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket.
Cool.
Shred in greased 13 x 9-inch dish. Mix soup, sour cream, butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add dash of salt and sugar.
Beat until real stiff.
Fold in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on foil and put on oven rack.
Preheat oven to 350°. After cookies are in oven, turn off oven and go to bed.
Next morning cookies are ready.
Do not open oven until ready to take out.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash squash; trim off ends.
Cut in chunks and cook in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Use small squash, not over 2 pounds.
After cooking, drain squash.
Put onion and sausage in skillet and cook until sausage is brown.
Drain off fat.
Use a little of the fat to oil casserole dish.
Combine squash, sausage, crumbs, beaten eggs, thyme, salt and half of cheese.
Put mixture in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes until thickened.
Add vanilla and gently stir in strawberries.
Slice bananas into bottom of baked crust and pour the strawberries and filling over bananas.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Top generously with Cool Whip.

title: chicken lettuce salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts 1/2 to 1 hour and sliver after cooked. Mix chicken, lettuce and onions a couple hours ahead of time.
Mix in seed, noodles and almonds right before serving.

title: unpotato salad(low carb)
directions: Put cauliflower in a microwave-safe casserole dish.
Add 1 Tbsp. water and cover.
Cook in microwave on high for 5 to 7 minutes and let stand, covered, another 3 to 5 minutes.
You want the cauliflower tender, but not mushy.
Drain cooked cauliflower and combine with celery and onion in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, Splenda and pepper.
Pour mixture over vegetables and mix well.
Mix in chopped eggs last; only stir lightly to preserve some small chunks of yolk.
Chill and serve. Serves 12.

title: apple cake
directions: Crumble butter and sugar.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and apple slices.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine, stir in rice until well mixed.
Pour in baking dish.
Add consomme and onion soup.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Cook mushrooms, carrots and onions in oil in a large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, sauce, olives and fennel.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: hawaii punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and pour over block of ice. Add chilled ginger ale just before serving. Add fresh fruit on top.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and stir over low heat until melted.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well and stir in pecans.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sesame noodle salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain well.
Toss with remaining ingredients. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Good for picnics.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: You will also need cupcake papers and muffin pans.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar.
Add flour and butter.
Put drained, sliced apples into a buttered oblong casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese topping is melted and bubbly.

title: ham-cheese appetizers
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Spread on slices of ham, roll lengthwise.
Refrigerate until firm and slice into bite-size pieces.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Simmer squash till tender; drain & sprinkle with salt. Combine egg yolks, sour cream, and flour; fold in egg whites. Place half the squash in a 12x7&1/2x2 inch baking dish. Top with half the egg mixture; half the cheese; and all the bacon. Repeat layers of squash, egg mixture, and cheese. Melt butter or margarine; stir in crumbs; sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: garlic baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Mince the garlic.
In a plate, mix the black pepper, oregano, salt, sazon, garlic and vinegar.
Mix well.
Brush on the chicken.
Spread it evenly all over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered, for 1/2 hour more uncovered.

title: apple scotch cookies
directions: Crem together brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, walnuts, raisins and butterscotch pieces.

title: yummy yummy year round cobbler
directions: Put raw fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the milk, alternately with the flour, baking powder and salt, which have been sifted together.
Put over raw fruit, then combine the topping and put over cake batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes, or until cake and fruit are done.
Serves 9.

title: pumpkin dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with vanilla and 1/2 cup milk as directed on package.
Combine 1 cup of prepared Dream Whip with pudding, 2/3 cup milk, pumpkin and cinnamon.
Beat slowly with eggbeater just until mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator until set, about 2 hours.
Cut and top each piece with Dream Whip.

title: broccoli strata
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, broccoli, rind and nutmeg.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is set.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburg stew
directions: Fry hamburg and onions in the oleo.
Add water, barley, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour more.

title: weeknight fajitas
directions: In large bowl, pour dressing over chicken, green pepper, onion, garlic and oregano.
Toss lightly and refrigerate at least 10 minutes.
Drain.
Stir-fry chicken mixture until chicken is browned and no longer pink.
Stir in tomato.
Wrap tortillas in dampened paper towels.
Microwave on High 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until softened.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture.
Serve with salsa, no-fat sour cream and no-fat Cheddar cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Fill each unbaked tart shell (see following recipe).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dust tops with powdered sugar when cool.

title: jamaican "curry goat"
directions: Dust veal in flour.
Brown veal in very hot oil.
Remove and toss in garlic and onion.
When onion is transparent, stir in curry powder, cumin, red pepper and ginger.
Cook, stirring over low heat.
Pour in chicken broth and bouillon and bring to simmer, stirring up all the browned bits with a wooden spoon.
Return meat to the skillet; baste with broth.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching and add water or stock if sauce seems too thick.
Stir in lime juice and season to taste with salt.
Just before serving, sprinkle with minced scallions.
Serve with chutney and small dishes of chopped egg yolk, chopped egg white, ground peanuts and shredded coconut.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken or turkey in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with rice and seasoning pack.
Add onion soup and water.
Top with mushroom soup.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti primavera salad with ham
directions: Prepare Creamettes spaghetti according to package directions, adding broccoli and carrot during last 2 minutes of cooking time; drain.
In large bowl, combine spaghetti, broccoli, carrot and next 3 ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Add Hormel chunk ham; toss to mix. Serve immediately or cover and chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together over low heat. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in square pan and cool.
Cut in squares.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add buttermilk, vanilla and raisins.
Mix well.
Add sugar and flour and mix well.
Cook on top of stove until thick, stirring to keep from burning.
Make meringue from egg whites.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties (3/4-inch thick).
Broil 3 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn and broil 4 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry dessert(preacher's delight)
directions: Cream 1/2 cup of sugar and margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pack down over bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl and stir well. Divide into 4 equal portions, shaping each into 1/2-inch patty. Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Place over medium heat until hot. Add patties and cook 6 minutes on each side until browned. Remove from skillet. Set aside and keep warm. Re-coat skillet with cooking spray. Add mushrooms. Saute over medium heat 3 minutes. Add consomm and Worcestershire sauce. Cook 10 minutes. Return patties to skillet. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Remove patties from skillet. Set aside and keep warm. Combine water and cornstarch. Stir well. Stir cornstarch mixture into broth mixture in skillet. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly. Spoon gravy over patties. Makes 4 servings (1 patty and about 6 tablespoons gravy).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over meat.
Bake until meat is done, basting occasionally.
(Will barbecue 3 to 4 pounds.)

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, except celery seed, adding the oil gradually and the vinegar in small amounts, each time adding the oil first and vinegar last.
Stir in celery seed last.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits on low heat, stirring occasionally until smooth. Add peanuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: pickled okra
directions: Sterilize jars and lids and keep in hot water until ready to use.
Pack okra in jar.
On top place 1 red pepper, 1 green chili pepper and 2 cloves garlic.
In small pan, combine vinegar, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil and pour over okra.
Let stand at room temperature.
Refrigerate 2 weeks before serving.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until apples are just tender.
Note:
Can use fresh fruit if in season.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Drain fruit cocktail, reserving juice.
Combine flour, sugar, eggs and juice in pan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Combine with shells; refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Mix in fruit and Cool Whip.
Ready to serve.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour over prebaked cake.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: starlight yellow cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly. Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: porcupine balls
directions: In a double boiler, combine caramel, milk and oleo.
Cook over water until caramel is melted; mix well.
Insert a toothpick in a marshmallow, roll in caramel mixture.
Drain excess caramel mixture off of marshmallow.
Then roll in Rice Krispies.
Pat the Rice Krispies well.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick butter, and eggs. Press into a 9 x 13 buttered and floured cake pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and add broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock barbecue
directions: Cook all ingredients until onion is tender.
Serve with rice, slaw or on a bun.

title: k. k.'s favorite salad
directions: Toss ingredients and serve.

title: viennese cherry cheese torte
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans. Combine mix, eggs, butter and water in a large mixer bowl.
Mix, bake and cool as directed on package of cake mix.
Refrigerate layers to make splitting easier.
Split each cake into 2 halves.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Heat oil.
When hot, add chopped onions, ginger and chilies. Saute the mixture on medium heat until the onions become tender. Add chopped tomatoes and all the spices.
Saute a few more minutes.
Add black-eyed peas; cook the mixture on medium heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water to prevent sticking.
Take away from heat and garnish with chopped cilantro.

title: pitzales
directions: In a large bowl, use pastry blender to work flour and shortening together to the consistency of coarse meal.
Set aside in refrigerator.

title: shirley's greek bread
directions: Combine mayonnaise, margarine, cheese, mushrooms, olives, onion, garlic powder and peppers.
Spread on French bread.
Bake until cheese is melted and bread is hot at 350°.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar together.
Add onions and blend in skillet.
Melt butter.
Place bread crumbs in butter and brown. In casserole dish, place one layer of bread crumbs.
Then one layer of tomato mixture.
Continue layering, ending with 1 layer of bread crumbs on top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: western omelet
directions: Beat eggs with water, salt and pepper.
Melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until soft (about 8 minutes).
Add beaten eggs and cook until light brown on bottom.
Fold and serve.

title: ham and sweet potato casserole
directions: Brown ham slightly in butter.
Whip potatoes until smooth and mix with eggs, milk, lemon juice and salt; whip again.
Mix with ham and drippings; turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk.
Put in microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Stir and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and cool.

title: satays - grilled beef, chicken or pork on skewers(from thailand)
directions: Soak 12-inch bamboo skewers in water for 1 hour to prevent burning.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans all night or at least 3 or 4 hours.
Put in pot and cover with water; add salt and boil.
Add cilantro, cumin, cayenne pepper and garlic.
Add ham, sausage or bacon pieces.
Cook until done.
Add water as needed, beans juice should be slightly thick.

title: breadstick alphabet dunkers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough; separate at perforations to form 8 strips.
On 1 large or 2 small ungreased cookie sheets, form each strip of dough into desired letter.
Brush with margarine.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, soda and peanut butter.
Mix well. Add sugars and cream together.
Add eggs, mixing well. Add flour and blend. Roll into balls.
Mash with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove 12 large outer leaves from cabbage.
Trim off thick part of each leaf.
Add leaves and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Allow to stand 5 minutes so they become pliable.
Drain. Combine onions, garlic, ground meat, rice, eggs, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place mound of meat mixture (about 1/2 cup) in hollow of each leaf.
Fold the sides of leaf over stuffing; roll up from the thick end of leaf to make a neat roll.
Arrange cabbage rolls, seam-side down, in a single layer in lightly buttered shallow, 3-quart baking pan.

title: carrot-date nut muffins
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and knead a bit until dough is earlobe consistency.
Cover the ball of dough with a bowl inverted on the counter and let dough sit 20 to 30 minutes.
You can make the rest of the dinner in the meantime.
Flour counter liberally. Heat a skillet to medium-high heat and break balls of dough about 1 1/2 to 2-inches in diameter.
One at a time, roll the balls out to about 4 to 5-inches in diameter and put the rolled chapatis into the heated dry skillet.
The chapatis should get little bubbles on the top surface in 15 to 20 seconds.
Using tongs, flip the chapati over to the other side and cook a few seconds.

title: almond amaretto cake
directions: In mixer whip butter until it is light and fluffy.
Add sugar, then almond and vanilla extracts.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add 1/3 cup flour mixture to the butter and sugar mixture, then 1/2 milk.
Blend well.
Add 1/3 more flour, the milk and then the last of the flour.
Mix well.
Whip egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold whites into cake mixture and divide into 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until cake is firm.
Let stand a few minutes and then remove from pans to cake racks to cool. Frost with Almond Butter Cream Frosting.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch casserole. Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cucumber pickles
directions: Have a large container of water boiling.
Drop cucumbers into water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove and pack into hot jars.
Add onion slices, garlic cloves, pepper and dill.
Boil water and vinegar and pour over mixture in jars.
Seal.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to package and drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese, mix well. Add grated cheese reserving 3/4 cups for top before baking.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (metal or glass).
You can either sprinkle cheese on top or mix cheese with bread crumbs and spread on top.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
If you mix the bread crumbs and cheese together, take foil off after one hour and continue baking 15 minutes.

title: fudge chocolate
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in large heavy saucepan.
Add milk and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball forms when a little is dropped in cold water.
You should be able to pick this ball up in your fingers.
Remove from heat and drop in margarine. Do not stir.
Cool until you can hold you hand on the bottom of the pan.
Stir until vanilla and margarine are mixed in and fudge loses its shine.
It will be very thick.
Add nuts.
Mix and pour in buttered pan.
Cut in squares.
Let cool and break apart.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix per package directions, adding cocoa before adding egg white mixture.
Fill cups with cake batter.
Mound tops slightly.
Stand in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on rack.
Store in airtight bags.
Frost and decorate.
Makes 24.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Use blender until creamy and thick.
Keeps in refrigerator for months.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Place meat and ginger ale in pan and simmer until liquid is about gone and meat is tender.
Flake meat with fork and add chili sauce and heat through.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Cream butter and cream cheese. Gradually
add
sugar, salt and vanilla, beating well. Alternately
add eggs and flour until mixed thoroughly. Pour batter into well-greased tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot fried chicken and dressing
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces; dip into flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients, using 1/2 cup soup to make dressing.
Arrange chicken on sides of greased crock-pot.
Pile dressing in center.
Make gravy of pan drippings, using 2 tablespoons flour and enough water with remaining soup to make 2 cups.
Pour over chicken and dressing. Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours on high temperature of crock-pot.

title: spicy cheeseburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first nine ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15--20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in beef and 2 C. of milk; heat through.
Combine flour and remaining milk until smooth; gradually stir into soup.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; stir in cheese until melted.
Add cayenne pepper to taste if desired.
Top with bacon just before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Purchase box of Pillsbury pumpkin bread.
Follow the directions on the box.
Impress your family and friends.

title: mae eide's pickled beets
directions: Boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite size pieces; this takes awhile. Marinate in lots and lots of apple cider.
Add spices to taste and enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks or until tender.
This will serve approximately 3,796 people.
If more are expected, add the two rabbits.
But do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Spread salad dressing over top to seal. Sprinkle 1 jar Romano cheese over this, then sprinkle 3 teaspoons sugar.
Refrigerate overnight or 12 hours.

title: garden patch meatball soup
directions: In large saucepan, stir together potatoes, carrots, onions, celery, tomatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaf and 3 cups water.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Mix together beef, egg and parsley.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Add to soup.
Simmer covered 15 minutes or until meatballs are tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and one egg at a time.
Beat. Add baking soda, flour, bananas and nuts. Mix well.
Turn into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden.
